16:51.432 --> 16:52.565
Why is it so famous

16:52.565 --> 16:54.231
when many people can draw this way?

16:54.565 --> 16:56.064
You think you could do an oil

16:56.064 --> 16:58.131
painting like Thomas Hart Benton?

16:58.197 --> 16:59.564
I'm not saying that I could,

16:59.797 --> 17:01.097
but I know others who could.

17:01.964 --> 17:03.897
Now, does anybody else have an opinion

17:04.196 --> 17:05.195
on the painting?

17:06.329 --> 17:07.363
It feels cold.

17:08.729 --> 17:10.162
The towering skyscrapers

17:10.162 --> 17:11.296
below a darkened sky.

17:12.628 --> 17:13.762
The American flag

17:13.762 --> 17:14.929
blowing in the wind, but

17:16.262 --> 17:17.162
the colors are muted.

17:18.560 --> 17:20.261
I like the way it feels stationary

17:20.594 --> 17:21.560
like the moment froze

17:21.560 --> 17:23.127
and he painted that way.

17:23.127 --> 17:24.961
It seems bleak, though,

17:24.961 --> 17:26.260
but at the same time

17:26.294 --> 17:27.294
saying that the artist

17:27.294 --> 17:28.260
was seeing things that way.

17:29.327 --> 17:29.893
Yeah.

17:31.160 --> 17:31.493
Yeah.

17:31.493 --> 17:33.159
Like he at that moment, maybe

17:33.926 --> 17:36.559
wanted to change or was battling

17:36.559 --> 17:37.692
something within himself.

17:38.025 --> 17:39.125
It shows that behind

17:39.125 --> 17:40.725
the beauty of the city is a danger.

17:41.525 --> 17:42.492
Maybe not everything

17:42.492 --> 17:43.425
is as it appears to be.

17:45.391 --> 17:49.657
Jimmy, Vivian, that was beautifully put.

18:03.055 --> 18:05.855
Jimmy, Jimmy, you got to light?

18:08.188 --> 18:09.155
Yeah, sure.

18:13.121 --> 18:14.287
You know, I really enjoyed

18:14.287 --> 18:15.154
your class today.

18:16.320 --> 18:17.287
It's nice to have a teacher

18:17.287 --> 18:18.387
that knows about the subject

18:18.387 --> 18:19.120
that they're teaching.

18:19.320 --> 18:20.853
Well, thank you very much.

18:21.886 --> 18:24.019
You know, you seem to understand

18:24.019 --> 18:25.452
it quite well yourself.

18:26.052 --> 18:27.885
Well, when you spend a lot of time alone,

18:29.119 --> 18:30.085
gives you time to read.

18:31.185 --> 18:32.485
Jimmy, can I say something?

18:32.951 --> 18:33.318
Sure.

18:34.451 --> 18:35.818
Your eye for the arts

18:35.818 --> 18:38.384
is really rather extraordinary.

18:39.251 --> 18:41.084
You seem to see things like somebody...

18:41.117 --> 18:41.584
Older?

18:41.917 --> 18:43.050
Older, yes.

18:43.583 --> 18:44.850
Comforts me, honestly.

18:45.983 --> 18:46.950
Sometimes I think

18:46.950 --> 18:48.116
the real world can seem so.

18:48.116 --> 18:50.449
grey, so...

18:50.449 --> 18:53.815
Noisy? Yeah.

18:54.715 --> 18:56.082
Yeah, exactly.

18:56.148 --> 18:59.048
But well, if you look at a painting

18:59.048 --> 19:00.948
like Van Gogh's Cafe

19:00.948 --> 19:02.181
Terrace at Night, well,

19:03.447 --> 19:07.047
colours the soothing yet

19:07.514 --> 19:09.547
vibrant feelings that it gives you.

19:11.646 --> 19:13.013
Well, that's my escapism.

19:14.213 --> 19:16.246
What got you into art Jimmy?

19:16.246 --> 19:16.812
My mother.

19:18.312 --> 19:19.245
I was just a kid.

19:19.945 --> 19:20.545
I remember her

19:20.545 --> 19:21.645
sat in the kitchen painting,

19:23.645 --> 19:24.711
she used to always say that

19:24.711 --> 19:26.311
the light in the kitchen was perfect,

19:26.311 --> 19:28.511
and you must have good natural light.

19:30.477 --> 19:31.910
I'd sit and watch her for hours.

19:33.310 --> 19:34.010
I'd look at the bliss

19:34.010 --> 19:35.610
on her face like she just

19:36.843 --> 19:37.476
vanished.

19:38.643 --> 19:40.043
Into her own magical world.

19:41.409 --> 19:42.709
Well, you know, maybe that's something

19:42.709 --> 19:45.142
you should take up for yourself.

19:45.742 --> 19:47.008
Live your passion.

19:47.008 --> 19:47.941
I said, I loved art,

19:48.375 --> 19:49.675
I didn't say I could paint,

19:49.675 --> 19:51.241
and trust me, I can't.

19:51.774 --> 19:55.074
Plus guys like me from this place.

19:57.507 --> 19:58.240
Well art exactly ain't In my future.

19:59.507 --> 20:00.373
Where is your mother?

20:01.473 --> 20:03.106
She skipped out on us when I was little,

20:03.106 --> 20:04.373
so I got stuck with him.

20:07.172 --> 20:09.239
God, I'm sorry, it's your first day

20:09.239 --> 20:10.938
here, and I'm troubling you with my woes.

20:11.638 --> 20:12.838
I found my husband in bed

20:12.838 --> 20:14.138
with another woman last night.

20:19.504 --> 20:20.337
I'm sorry. I.

20:20.337 --> 20:23.103
I don't know why I told you that.

20:26.970 --> 20:27.536
You know,

20:29.136 --> 20:30.969
you're not like the women around here.

20:31.269 --> 20:32.369
Jimmy, Jimmy.

20:33.002 --> 20:34.202
Hey, Jimmy, you ready to go?

20:34.402 --> 20:35.502
Yeah, sure. I'm just talking to Mrs.....

20:35.502 --> 20:35.902
Have you seen Vivian?

20:35.902 --> 20:38.468
Not since class,

20:38.468 --> 20:39.535
oh wait here she comes, control yourself.

20:39.535 --> 20:41.734
Vivian you look as beautiful

20:41.734 --> 20:42.201
as a bright summers day.

20:42.201 --> 20:44.034
Shut up Riff.

20:44.034 --> 20:44.901
Mrs Smart .

20:45.067 --> 20:46.700
I really enjoyed your class today.

20:46.734 --> 20:48.000
It was very uplifting.

20:48.033 --> 20:49.067
Uplifting?

20:49.067 --> 20:50.966
Well, thank you very much, Betty.

20:51.266 --> 20:52.033
Umm Mrs. Smart.

20:52.333 --> 20:53.166
Can I just say that?

20:53.233 --> 20:53.799
Wow.

20:54.299 --> 20:55.732
You look like a movie star.

20:56.199 --> 20:58.132
Well, so I've been told.

20:58.132 --> 21:00.232
Actually I am an actress.

21:00.498 --> 21:02.465
What, like in the movies?

21:02.498 --> 21:03.098
Sure.

21:03.431 --> 21:05.031
Well, only a few small roles,

21:05.031 --> 21:07.231
but I have done many plays.

21:07.631 --> 21:10.164
One critic once called me dazzling.

21:10.331 --> 21:12.164
Dazzling. Wow.

21:12.497 --> 21:14.363
That's my dream, to be somebody

21:14.363 --> 21:15.563
that people talk about

21:15.596 --> 21:16.930
my face on the big screen.

21:17.196 --> 21:20.163
You would look magnificent Vivian,

21:20.163 --> 21:20.263
a real bombshell.

21:20.296 --> 21:21.796
Oh, you really think so, Riff?

21:21.796 --> 21:22.696
Sure thing.

21:22.696 --> 21:23.462
Well, you know,

21:23.462 --> 21:25.129
I was actually thinking about

21:25.529 --> 21:26.395
perhaps teaching,

21:26.395 --> 21:28.728
acting to people like you, young people

21:28.728 --> 21:30.728
who you want to make it in the movies.

21:31.094 --> 21:32.228
Oh, this is smart.

21:32.228 --> 21:33.527
I mean, I would love that.

21:33.661 --> 21:34.827
Well, money.

21:34.894 --> 21:36.360
My mother. Oh, baby.

21:36.360 --> 21:38.427
And I wouldn't dream of charging.

21:39.093 --> 21:40.560
Everybody deserves a shot.

21:40.826 --> 21:41.293
Oh, Mrs.

21:41.293 --> 21:42.626
Smart, then I would love to.

21:42.793 --> 21:43.626
Oh, you have no idea

21:43.626 --> 21:44.693
how happy this makes me.

21:46.126 --> 21:46.626
How about you, Jimmy?

21:46.626 --> 21:49.692
You have a face the camera would love.

21:51.092 --> 21:51.592
Really?

21:52.925 --> 21:53.825
Well, I don't know

21:53.825 --> 21:55.558
about all that acting stuff, but

21:56.391 --> 21:57.991
I'd sure love to sit and listen to

21:57.991 --> 21:58.757
you talk about it.

21:59.457 --> 22:00.291
Can I come, too?

22:00.524 --> 22:02.290
I'm a real movie picture fan, you know.

22:02.357 --> 22:03.923
Oh, well, sure.

22:03.957 --> 22:05.823
Well, this sounds like a plan.

22:06.023 --> 22:07.923
So why don't we say my place

22:07.923 --> 22:09.923
tomorrow night, say 7:00?

22:10.089 --> 22:11.289
What will your husband say?

22:11.422 --> 22:12.522
Well, he's working

22:12.522 --> 22:13.822
very late tomorrow night,

22:13.822 --> 22:16.022
so we'll have the place to ourselves.

22:16.055 --> 22:17.955
Well, I will be there with bells on.

22:18.221 --> 22:20.288
Oh, maybe you could show me

22:20.388 --> 22:21.788
how to make my hair like yours.

22:22.254 --> 22:26.554
I think I would trade

22:26.554 --> 22:28.154
in my best friend to look like you.

22:28.154 --> 22:29.387
Wait, What? Vivian Pierce, where are you?

22:29.387 --> 22:30.653
Great! Mother.

22:30.953 --> 22:32.286
I was just talking to Mrs.

22:32.286 --> 22:32.653
Smart.

22:32.686 --> 22:33.819
She's my new teacher

22:33.819 --> 22:35.486
and she's an actress.

22:35.886 --> 22:37.386
It's lovely to meet you.

22:38.352 --> 22:39.519
Charmed, I'm sure.

22:40.885 --> 22:41.852
Now, Vivian, Betty

22:41.852 --> 22:42.818
let's go

22:42.818 --> 22:44.385
we're having an early supper tonight

22:44.385 --> 22:45.218
before your father heads

22:45.218 --> 22:47.184
off to work late, again.

22:47.518 --> 22:48.351
Mrs Smart .

22:48.917 --> 22:50.551
I can't wait for us to begin our lessons.

22:53.983 --> 22:54.883
Mrs. Smart.

22:56.750 --> 22:57.450
Boys.

23:02.282 --> 23:04.215
I don't think she liked me very much.

23:04.815 --> 23:06.082
She doesn't like anybody,

23:06.415 --> 23:11.114
including her own husband.

23:11.114 --> 23:15.181
Poor schlep.

23:15.181 --> 23:16.214
I'd always had problems

23:16.214 --> 23:17.480
in the neighborhood where kids

23:17.480 --> 23:18.747
like Jimmy and Riff lived.

23:19.513 --> 23:20.447
It wasn't the safest

23:20.447 --> 23:21.613
of places in the town.

23:22.013 --> 23:24.446
Poverty was the word of the day,

23:24.446 --> 23:26.112
the kind of place the rest of the town

23:26.112 --> 23:27.512
looked down on like a blemish

23:28.179 --> 23:29.045
that wouldn't go away.

23:29.879 --> 23:31.178
I think she looked at me today.

23:31.645 --> 23:32.745
Who? Vivian.

23:33.212 --> 23:34.411
I swear she did, Jimmy.

23:34.411 --> 23:35.145
She looked round

23:35.245 --> 23:37.044
and for a moment, our eyes connected.

23:37.144 --> 23:38.711
I think you see what you want to see.

23:39.011 --> 23:40.511
Trust me, I've known her for years.

23:40.511 --> 23:41.610
You've known for years.

23:41.977 --> 23:42.844
When has she ever shown

23:42.844 --> 23:44.177
any interest in a guy like you?

23:44.210 --> 23:45.410
What do you mean a guy like me?

23:45.443 --> 23:46.576
What kind of crack is that?

23:46.576 --> 23:47.910
No crack. It's cool.

23:47.910 --> 23:49.709
It's just... It's just what?

23:49.709 --> 23:50.543
Come on Riff,

23:50.543 --> 23:51.742
you've been loopy for Vivian

23:51.742 --> 23:52.642
since we were 10 years

23:52.642 --> 23:53.775
old, it's time to move on.

23:53.875 --> 23:55.309
Go swivel Jimmy.

23:56.508 --> 23:57.942
Pair of aces.

23:59.675 --> 24:02.874
Damn it, man.

24:02.874 --> 24:04.007
I can't concentrate.

24:04.241 --> 24:06.007
My mind feels like cotton candy.

24:06.374 --> 24:08.040
I mean, it wasn't just me, right?

24:08.773 --> 24:09.573
Mrs Smart is...

24:09.573 --> 24:10.773
A babe?

24:10.773 --> 24:11.440
A doll?

24:11.440 --> 24:13.440
Yeah, but it's more than that,

24:13.440 --> 24:14.539
before you turned up

24:14.539 --> 24:15.473
we were really talking.

24:16.872 --> 24:17.206
Man.

24:17.272 --> 24:18.539
She's like a hundred?

24:18.705 --> 24:19.972
No, Jesus.

24:19.972 --> 24:21.905
She's like 40 I bet.

24:21.905 --> 24:22.805
That's a woman who's

24:22.805 --> 24:23.838
seen a lot of things.

24:23.871 --> 24:24.271
Yeah.

24:24.405 --> 24:26.204
Like the backseat in many a Chevrolet.

24:26.238 --> 24:27.304
Hey don't talk that way.

24:28.904 --> 24:30.837
You shouldn't talk that way about a lady.

24:31.204 --> 24:33.837
She's taken Jimmy,

24:33.837 --> 24:34.670
did you not see the rock on her finger,

24:34.670 --> 24:36.636
He's a deadbeat, he cheats on her?

24:36.936 --> 24:38.470
Wait she told you this?

24:38.503 --> 24:40.136
Yeah, I told you we talked.

24:41.169 --> 24:41.536
Damn it.

24:41.536 --> 24:42.836
I can't wait to see her tomorrow.

24:42.936 --> 24:45.869
Oh you are lost to the darkside

24:45.869 --> 24:46.702
my friend. Darkside?

24:46.968 --> 24:47.835
Women.

24:47.835 --> 24:48.502
And Vivien?

24:48.768 --> 24:49.968
It's Destiny.

24:53.434 --> 24:55.867
Seeing her today just made me realise

24:56.001 --> 24:57.167
girls, they don't know anything

24:57.167 --> 24:59.267
about life, love,

25:00.567 --> 25:01.866
sex... Sex.

25:02.000 --> 25:02.700
You think you're going to be

25:02.700 --> 25:04.166
playing backseat bingo with her?

25:04.166 --> 25:05.299
No, you clown.

25:05.299 --> 25:05.966
I'm just saying that

25:05.966 --> 25:07.066
today opened my eyes.

25:07.066 --> 25:07.799
I mean, come on.

25:08.765 --> 25:10.032
She's like something from a movie.

25:10.799 --> 25:12.098
Well, Jimmy, as much fun

25:12.098 --> 25:13.565
as it is, I really got to go.

25:13.598 --> 25:14.631
I'm going to miss the best time.

25:14.665 --> 25:15.065
Riff,

25:16.198 --> 25:17.464
I can speak to my old man.

25:18.431 --> 25:19.831
See if you can stay with us.

25:19.831 --> 25:20.731
You don't deserve to

25:20.731 --> 25:21.697
be out on the street.

25:21.697 --> 25:22.530
You got to be able to...

25:22.530 --> 25:23.697
I know, Jimmy, you've

25:23.697 --> 25:24.763
given me the same speech

25:24.763 --> 25:25.463
since the funeral.

25:25.463 --> 25:26.996
But I'm fine. Really?

25:27.263 --> 25:28.729
I got everything under control.

25:28.763 --> 25:30.563
Yeah, but I got this, Jimmy.

25:32.629 --> 25:34.695
Sleeping down the docks again tonight?

25:34.695 --> 25:36.795
Yeah, I found this great old building.

25:37.062 --> 25:38.562
I share it with like 300 bats.

25:38.628 --> 25:39.095
Shut up.

25:39.361 --> 25:39.795
You hear that?

25:41.861 --> 25:42.961
Oh, shit.

25:42.961 --> 25:44.261
My dad's home. Jimmy!

25:45.594 --> 25:46.594
So this is what happens

25:46.594 --> 25:47.294
when I'm not here?

25:47.527 --> 25:47.960
No.

25:49.093 --> 25:49.260
You just thought you would

25:49.260 --> 25:50.593
steal my cigarettes

25:50.793 --> 25:51.693
and act like a big man

25:51.693 --> 25:52.493
when I ain't around.

25:53.426 --> 25:54.126
I should go.

25:54.126 --> 25:55.559
It's lovely to see you, Mr. Flynn.

25:55.559 --> 25:56.392
May I say you are looking

25:56.392 --> 25:57.592
particularly rugged today.

25:57.592 --> 25:57.826
Get out!

26:02.492 --> 26:03.325
I'm going to go to my room.

26:03.791 --> 26:04.191
Why?

26:05.758 --> 26:07.158
You scared of your old man?

26:08.291 --> 26:08.924
No, sir.

26:08.991 --> 26:09.524
I just.

26:09.524 --> 26:10.957
So you think you're a man now

26:10.957 --> 26:13.424
because you started smoking cigarettes?

26:14.557 --> 26:15.023
Go on.

26:16.190 --> 26:18.123
Show me how much of a man you really are.

26:18.123 --> 26:18.823
Leave me alone.

26:19.556 --> 26:21.123
You know, we should put a dress on you

26:21.123 --> 26:21.889
so anyone can see

26:21.889 --> 26:23.689
how much of a girl you are.

26:23.689 --> 26:24.355
Look at you,

26:25.755 --> 26:27.055
you dress like some rebel

26:27.588 --> 26:28.555
but you,

26:29.021 --> 26:29.988
you're as soft as a newborn

26:29.988 --> 26:30.955
babies backside.

26:34.621 --> 26:35.587
Oh, wait.

26:35.587 --> 26:36.654
I need you down at the garage

26:36.720 --> 26:37.287
tomorrow night,

26:37.354 --> 26:39.220
we've got two cars coming in

26:39.220 --> 26:40.153
that need to be finished.

26:42.186 --> 26:42.520
Sure.

26:44.253 --> 26:46.519
Oh, no, I can't.

26:46.519 --> 26:47.519
I've already made plans.

26:49.152 --> 26:49.619
Plans?

26:50.185 --> 26:50.985
You don't have plans

26:50.985 --> 26:51.952
you're just a kid.

26:52.085 --> 26:53.152
I'm sixteen.

26:54.351 --> 26:54.951
I'm sorry, Dad,

26:54.951 --> 26:56.151
but I can't make it tomorrow.

26:56.918 --> 26:58.084
Oh, you will be there,

26:58.084 --> 27:00.517
or you can pack up your stuff

27:00.784 --> 27:02.517
and see how you do out there on the street

27:02.517 --> 27:03.317
Dad please.

27:03.317 --> 27:04.717
You are sixteen Jimmy,

27:05.383 --> 27:06.283
it's time to be a man

27:06.283 --> 27:07.483
and make an honest wage.

27:07.850 --> 27:08.550
You can't expect me

27:08.550 --> 27:09.683
to have you here living forever.

27:12.482 --> 27:14.515
Now, go to your room and stay there,

27:15.282 --> 27:15.882
I got a friend

27:15.882 --> 27:16.482
coming over tonight

27:16.482 --> 27:18.315
and I do not want to be disturbed.

27:18.315 --> 27:18.915
A woman?

27:20.581 --> 27:22.048
None of your goddamn business,

27:24.181 --> 27:25.481
you don't even know what a woman is.

27:28.347 --> 27:29.447
Now get out of my sight.

27:33.346 --> 27:35.013
Yes sir.

27:46.544 --> 27:47.744
At Vivian's house.

27:48.378 --> 27:49.811
Well, Vivian was brought up

27:49.811 --> 27:50.977
under the eyes of God,

27:51.544 --> 27:52.977
a devout kind of family,

27:53.010 --> 27:54.710
a cross on the wall

27:54.710 --> 27:56.277
and a Bible on the nightstand.

27:56.843 --> 27:58.710
But Vivian is a teenage girl

27:59.443 --> 28:00.909
starting to question things.

28:01.976 --> 28:02.909
I'm glad your mother

28:02.909 --> 28:04.209
let me stay over Vivian.

28:04.342 --> 28:05.975
Oh, me too.

28:05.975 --> 28:07.442
Plus, I know it's

28:07.442 --> 28:08.642
your father's cards night?

28:09.108 --> 28:11.008
His friends give me the heebie jeebies.

28:13.774 --> 28:15.641
Betty, do you think I could ever look

28:15.641 --> 28:16.740
like Veronica Smart?

28:17.307 --> 28:18.407
Vivian, you've not stopped

28:18.407 --> 28:20.073
talking about her since we left school.

28:20.107 --> 28:21.706
Sorry Betty, it's just

28:21.706 --> 28:23.106
I've only ever seen women

28:23.106 --> 28:23.906
like her in the pages

28:23.906 --> 28:25.239
of our celebrity magazine.

28:25.673 --> 28:27.639
Imagine a woman like that.

28:27.639 --> 28:29.405
Living right here in our town.

28:29.905 --> 28:31.672
You sound screwy Vivian Pierce.

28:31.972 --> 28:33.772
It's not like she's Lana Turner.

28:34.638 --> 28:36.638
Oh she was so perfect.

28:36.971 --> 28:38.638
OK, I'm officially ignoring you.

28:39.237 --> 28:40.337
Sorry, Betty.

28:40.704 --> 28:41.504
You are going to come to hers

28:41.504 --> 28:42.337
tomorrow, though, of course.

28:42.770 --> 28:43.704
No way.

28:44.004 --> 28:45.470
My mother would flip her wig.

28:45.770 --> 28:47.170
She thinks that actors

28:47.170 --> 28:48.003
are lower than whores.

28:48.570 --> 28:50.036
Her words, not mine.

28:50.403 --> 28:53.169
Well, I think your mother and my mother

28:53.202 --> 28:54.369
are the same person.

28:56.169 --> 28:57.735
I'm going to brush my teeth.

28:58.068 --> 28:59.401
It's spearmint!

29:01.568 --> 29:03.401
Oooh, I'm sorry Mrs Pierce.

29:05.634 --> 29:07.834
Now, Vivien, I need to talk to you.

29:08.467 --> 29:09.400
Am I in trouble?

29:10.067 --> 29:12.066
No, I'm worried about you.

29:12.066 --> 29:13.133
And so is your father.

29:13.200 --> 29:14.899
You come home from school and disappear

29:14.933 --> 29:15.966
so fast to your room

29:15.966 --> 29:17.299
that we barely get a hello.

29:17.699 --> 29:19.565
I'm fine, mother, honestly.

29:19.999 --> 29:21.099
It's just.

29:23.332 --> 29:24.265
Oh Vivian, it's just what?

29:25.998 --> 29:28.431
Well, when did you first start

29:28.431 --> 29:30.831
to get feelings for boys?

29:31.331 --> 29:33.564
You know, in the non friend way?

29:34.830 --> 29:35.897
Vivian, you are too young

29:35.897 --> 29:36.830
to be thinking about that.

29:36.863 --> 29:38.663
I'm fifteen mother, please.

29:39.529 --> 29:40.896
There is a time and place for a man

29:41.029 --> 29:42.396
and that time is not now.

29:43.396 --> 29:44.662
Do you want to end up like the neighbours

29:44.662 --> 29:46.629
daughter out all hours, drinking,

29:46.629 --> 29:47.395
cavorting around

29:47.395 --> 29:48.795
with every boy that looks at her?

29:48.862 --> 29:50.595
Sure sounds more fun than this.

29:51.195 --> 29:51.561
Look.

29:53.861 --> 29:55.061
I know I sound harsh,

29:55.494 --> 29:56.327
and I'm not saying

29:56.327 --> 29:56.927
that when you're older,

29:56.927 --> 29:58.394
you can't make your own choices,

29:58.394 --> 29:59.993
but I have to guide you now

29:59.993 --> 30:00.727
so those choices

30:00.727 --> 30:02.360
you make in the future are good ones.

30:02.793 --> 30:04.393
Worrying about boys and playing this

30:04.393 --> 30:05.393
kind of music is most

30:05.393 --> 30:06.593
certainly not a good one.

30:06.759 --> 30:08.426
It's just music, mother.

30:08.626 --> 30:09.792
I don't think Satan plans

30:09.792 --> 30:10.692
on coming through my record player

30:10.692 --> 30:11.659
to corrupt me.

30:12.658 --> 30:12.792
Vivian!

30:12.792 --> 30:14.058
You are not too old to be put over

30:14.058 --> 30:14.725
your father's knee.

30:14.891 --> 30:15.858
Sorry, mother.

30:18.358 --> 30:19.091
You just need to say

30:19.091 --> 30:20.091
your prayers before bed.

30:20.491 --> 30:21.224
Go to church.

30:21.557 --> 30:22.490
Study hard.

30:22.490 --> 30:24.323
And then you can think about a husband.

30:24.390 --> 30:26.690
But mother, if I'm too young to date,

30:26.690 --> 30:28.123
surely I'm too young to think

30:28.123 --> 30:28.823
about a husband.

30:29.056 --> 30:29.523
Vivian.

30:29.523 --> 30:30.856
Nobody likes a smart mouth.

30:30.856 --> 30:33.056
Now turn those records off

30:33.089 --> 30:34.422
It's time for bed for you two.

30:34.422 --> 30:36.789
Oh no, five more minutes mother, please.

30:38.055 --> 30:38.922
Fine.

30:39.555 --> 30:41.855
Five more minutes then bed.

30:41.855 --> 30:42.254
OK.

30:45.121 --> 30:47.387
Oh, sorry Mrs Pierce.

30:48.187 --> 30:49.920
Oh Vivian,

30:50.087 --> 30:51.220
I forgot to mention,

30:51.420 --> 30:52.520
I think I know who was going

30:52.520 --> 30:53.386
to ask you to the dance.

30:54.386 --> 30:55.186
Do you think she would let me

30:55.186 --> 30:56.286
try on one of her dresses?

30:56.519 --> 30:58.619
Oh, I bet she gets them from Europe.

30:59.119 --> 31:00.519
OK, good night, Vivian.

31:01.085 --> 31:02.352
Sorry, Betty.

31:05.518 --> 31:06.518
After catching Cliff

31:06.518 --> 31:08.018
and Lana in the sinful act,

31:08.451 --> 31:10.017
something in Veronica changed

31:10.617 --> 31:11.551
or maybe just brought

31:11.551 --> 31:12.817
the real her to the surface.

31:13.517 --> 31:15.883
Either way, the kids were so blinded

31:15.883 --> 31:17.316
by her, they wouldn't see anything

31:17.316 --> 31:18.883
the dame wouldn't allow them to see.

31:19.983 --> 31:21.149
It's the evening after

31:21.149 --> 31:22.616
and Cliff is away with work.

31:23.582 --> 31:25.749
Veronica, well Veronica

31:25.749 --> 31:27.648
is dressed like a goddamn lounge

31:27.648 --> 31:29.382
singer, wearing a bright red dress,

31:29.815 --> 31:32.581
showing off all her killer curves.

31:34.714 --> 31:36.514
Anybody order a group of street rats?

31:36.514 --> 31:38.414
Speak for yourself Riff Randall.

31:38.414 --> 31:39.613
I am so pleased you could all make it,

31:39.613 --> 31:40.847
come in.

31:41.013 --> 31:41.613
Woah!

31:41.647 --> 31:42.646
You've got a real nice

31:42.646 --> 31:44.013
pile of bricks here Mrs Smart.

31:44.013 --> 31:45.813
Oh, please call me Veronica.

31:45.813 --> 31:46.913
OK, Veronica.

31:47.212 --> 31:49.046
Now, who would like a drink,

31:49.079 --> 31:50.912
something to get this party started?

31:50.945 --> 31:51.812
Alcoholic?

31:51.879 --> 31:53.245
I won't tell anyone if you won't.

31:53.245 --> 31:54.945
Then I'll have a beer.

31:55.245 --> 31:56.145
How about you two?

31:56.145 --> 31:58.844
Oh, no, just a lemonade for me, please.

31:58.878 --> 31:59.811
Sure. You got whiskey?

32:00.111 --> 32:01.044
I do indeed.

32:01.044 --> 32:02.977
So I heard your old man

32:02.977 --> 32:03.844
is stepping out on you.

32:04.277 --> 32:04.910
Riff, Jesus.

32:04.943 --> 32:06.243
No, it's fine, honestly.

32:06.777 --> 32:07.776
Men are pigs.

32:07.776 --> 32:08.176
(Pig noises)

32:08.743 --> 32:09.709
Mrs. Smart?

32:09.709 --> 32:11.743
Um, I mean, Veronica,

32:12.009 --> 32:13.742
your dress is so magnificent.

32:13.976 --> 32:15.309
Oh, what? This old thing.

32:15.542 --> 32:17.608
Oh, I would love a dress like that.

32:17.942 --> 32:18.842
And your hair.

32:19.275 --> 32:20.975
How do you get it to look so glamorous?

32:21.675 --> 32:22.274
Vivian.

32:22.441 --> 32:25.741
Well, I think you have a beautiful face,

32:26.107 --> 32:28.740
stunning bone structure, and those eyes.

32:29.040 --> 32:30.740
They could melt the heart of a sailor.

32:30.840 --> 32:32.740
Oh, oh, oh.

32:33.073 --> 32:35.439
Ok Vivian, relax.

32:35.439 --> 32:36.906
I could relax you, Vivian.

32:36.906 --> 32:37.606
Ewww.

32:37.606 --> 32:40.239
Do I see a little love connection here?

32:40.305 --> 32:41.039
Flirtation?

32:41.239 --> 32:42.205
No, you do not.

32:42.338 --> 32:43.772
Riff has been trying to get me to go

32:43.772 --> 32:44.671
steady with him since

32:44.671 --> 32:45.838
we're six years old.

32:46.038 --> 32:47.371
He's not my type.

32:47.471 --> 32:49.338
Maybe you don't know what your type is.

32:49.937 --> 32:51.171
So how about you, Jimmy?

32:51.171 --> 32:53.504
You got a lady in your life?

32:53.970 --> 32:55.937
Girls my age aren't appealing to me.

32:56.970 --> 32:57.436
I'm going to wait

32:57.436 --> 32:59.136
till after high school to find my girl.

32:59.303 --> 32:59.936
I see.

33:00.203 --> 33:01.236
Can I get another drink?

33:01.469 --> 33:02.802
Oh, sure, help yourself.

33:02.936 --> 33:04.536
But just don't let your parents know

33:04.536 --> 33:05.835
I'm letting you drink liquor.

33:06.369 --> 33:07.069
Can I smoke?

33:07.135 --> 33:07.802
Sure.

33:08.302 --> 33:10.301
As long as I can bum one from you.

33:11.168 --> 33:12.934
Can I bum one also?

33:17.001 --> 33:25.566
Here, Vivian, let me light it for you.

33:25.566 --> 33:27.299
I think I'll save this for later.

33:27.932 --> 33:30.132
So, Jimmy, when you're alone,

33:30.532 --> 33:31.765
what is it you like to do?

33:33.598 --> 33:35.931
Listen to music, read books,

33:36.965 --> 33:37.664
play my guitar.

33:38.464 --> 33:39.298
Oh the guitar.

33:39.598 --> 33:40.697
I play the violin.

33:40.964 --> 33:42.797
Oh really, well the violin,

33:42.830 --> 33:45.197
the guitar, hell even the goddamn drums.

33:45.530 --> 33:47.030
I think it's all wonderful.

33:47.263 --> 33:49.263
Hey, Riff, turn up the music.

33:49.496 --> 33:50.829
Let's dance.

33:50.863 --> 33:52.063
What? Here, now?

33:52.362 --> 33:55.062
Here and now is all we have Jimmy Flynn.

33:56.362 --> 33:57.528
Veronica, Riff and Jimmy

33:57.528 --> 33:58.662
danced around the room.

33:59.462 --> 34:01.595
Veronica looked happy and the kids ate up

34:01.595 --> 34:03.194
that happiness with a silver spoon.

34:04.128 --> 34:05.294
Jimmy played it cool,

34:05.861 --> 34:07.360
leaning on the cabinet of trophys

34:07.360 --> 34:09.094
from her husband's college days.

34:09.793 --> 34:11.159
It's rude to stare, Jimmy.

34:11.193 --> 34:12.327
I'm sorry.

34:13.060 --> 34:14.393
The last man who stared at me

34:14.393 --> 34:15.759
that way, ended up laying

34:15.759 --> 34:18.159
beside me for the next 16 years.

34:18.559 --> 34:20.759
She got him!

34:20.759 --> 34:22.692
Oh, I'm so, so sorry.

34:22.692 --> 34:23.558
I'll clean all that up.

34:23.558 --> 34:24.824
It's fine, honestly.

34:24.925 --> 34:26.690
My husband, he breaks a lot of glasses.

34:26.891 --> 34:27.491
What's he doing?

34:27.491 --> 34:28.824
Throwing them around the house.

34:29.024 --> 34:31.956
In that moment, Veronica started to lie.

34:32.024 --> 34:33.590
Yeah. Sometimes he...

34:33.590 --> 34:35.657
He what?

34:35.657 --> 34:36.322
Never mind.

34:39.090 --> 34:40.789
Marriage is tough kids.

34:40.789 --> 34:43.289
You try so hard to

34:43.722 --> 34:45.188
to be the perfect housewife,

34:45.188 --> 34:46.188
and yet still it's

34:47.255 --> 34:48.355
it's never quite enough.

34:49.388 --> 34:52.121
He cheated, many times I suspect,

34:53.321 --> 34:54.721
he didn't even apologize.

34:54.721 --> 34:55.587
He just said that

34:56.687 --> 34:57.887
the man's got to do

34:58.420 --> 34:59.820
what a man's got to do.

35:00.787 --> 35:01.520
That's what he said.

35:03.120 --> 35:05.253
Listen to me bringing the party down.

35:05.786 --> 35:07.119
I'm so sorry whilst

35:07.119 --> 35:08.686
we are here in this house.

35:09.052 --> 35:10.885
Let's forget all the bad in our lives

35:10.885 --> 35:12.852
and just focus on the good.

35:13.385 --> 35:16.518
Oh, Veronica, I just wanted to ask,

35:16.618 --> 35:17.951
what movies have you starred in?

35:17.984 --> 35:19.951
Did you see Hunt for Love

35:20.284 --> 35:21.317
with Cary Grant?

35:21.651 --> 35:23.217
Oh, I love that movie.

35:23.317 --> 35:24.617
Well, I was the nurse

35:24.717 --> 35:26.583
who got him back to health.

35:26.583 --> 35:28.816
So you met him?

35:28.816 --> 35:30.883
Darling, met him? We're friends,

35:30.883 --> 35:32.483
we bonded over our love

35:32.483 --> 35:33.882
for the silent movies.

35:33.916 --> 35:34.782
Oh, Vivian.

35:35.149 --> 35:37.082
The stories I could tell you.

35:37.115 --> 35:38.782
Oh, I would love to hear them.

35:39.482 --> 35:42.281
So, Jimmy, you got a talent?

35:42.648 --> 35:43.814
Boosting cars?

35:43.814 --> 35:45.048
Mmm, a bad boy?

35:45.048 --> 35:46.114
I prefer rebel.

35:46.181 --> 35:47.081
You have ice?

35:47.081 --> 35:48.280
Sure it's in the kitchen.

35:48.314 --> 35:49.114
Help yourself.

35:49.114 --> 35:51.047
Vivian why don't you help

35:51.047 --> 35:52.280
Riff with the ice

35:52.280 --> 35:54.446
and maybe bring in some snacks?

35:54.913 --> 35:55.679
Sure thing.

35:55.979 --> 35:57.612
Veronica, why us?

35:58.712 --> 35:59.646
What do you mean Riff?

35:59.746 --> 36:01.379
Why would you want to be friends with us?

36:01.412 --> 36:01.679
I mean,

36:01.812 --> 36:03.612
you're a beautiful, wealthy woman.

36:03.812 --> 36:06.145
We're hardly your usual crowd.

36:06.945 --> 36:07.944
Honestly,

36:07.944 --> 36:10.677
I never really fit in around here.

36:12.211 --> 36:13.210
Housewives, they look

36:13.210 --> 36:16.243
at me like I'm trash and the men

36:16.243 --> 36:17.843
look at me with lustful eyes.

36:19.110 --> 36:19.543
I guess

36:20.709 --> 36:21.843
I just needed a change

36:21.843 --> 36:22.742
of energy around me.

36:27.042 --> 36:27.475
You know,

36:27.475 --> 36:28.908
you have a really neat set of records.

36:29.242 --> 36:29.908
Oh, thanks.

36:30.875 --> 36:32.808
My husband hates them of course.

36:33.374 --> 36:34.274
He's not really that big

36:34.274 --> 36:37.840
into the music or movies or art.

36:38.374 --> 36:39.407
He's a bit square when it comes

36:39.407 --> 36:40.074
to those things.

36:40.740 --> 36:41.540
You like this one?

36:42.607 --> 36:43.106
Sure.

36:50.172 --> 36:51.539
Tell me more about you, Jimmy.

36:53.738 --> 36:54.605
What do you want to know?

36:55.805 --> 36:56.405
Everything.

36:59.104 --> 37:00.871
Well, I'm 16,

37:00.871 --> 37:03.104
but I think I'm more mature my age.

37:05.937 --> 37:09.003
I ride a motorcycle.

37:10.303 --> 37:11.436
So, are you going to come over here

37:11.436 --> 37:12.802
and dance with me

37:12.802 --> 37:14.702
or you just going to leave

37:14.702 --> 37:17.402
this girl dancing all by herself.

37:21.735 --> 37:23.801
I love to dance.

37:24.168 --> 37:25.134
I love to dance with a man

37:25.134 --> 37:26.934
who loves to dance.

37:28.334 --> 37:30.000
It's been a long time.

37:30.367 --> 37:31.700
Forgive me for saying

37:31.700 --> 37:34.033
but why not just ditch the loser

37:34.033 --> 37:35.399
if he ain't keeping your engine running?

37:35.899 --> 37:38.166
Oh, Jimmy, it's not as simple as that.

37:39.032 --> 37:40.465
Let's just forget about him.

37:41.532 --> 37:42.565
Let's just pretend that

37:43.298 --> 37:46.265
nobody in the whole world is around.

37:47.598 --> 37:48.898
We just keep on dancing.

37:50.198 --> 37:51.164
Your smell it's.

37:51.164 --> 37:51.497
It's

37:53.997 --> 37:55.164
quite intoxicating.

37:55.630 --> 37:57.430
You smell of cigarette

37:57.430 --> 37:59.096
smoke, liquor and

38:00.563 --> 38:01.329
engine fumes.

38:01.329 --> 38:02.229
I'm sorry.

38:02.663 --> 38:07.429
Don't be, I love that smell.

38:08.295 --> 38:10.495
Jimmy, when you go out on your bike

38:10.495 --> 38:12.261
where is it you go to?

38:13.728 --> 38:14.628
I know a spot

38:15.661 --> 38:17.494
out by the woods near the cemetery.

38:17.527 --> 38:18.494
It's quiet.

38:19.827 --> 38:20.760
Gives me time to think

38:21.893 --> 38:24.460
Maybe I need a spot like that.

38:24.460 --> 38:25.326
I can take you to mine.

38:26.026 --> 38:27.793
On your bike?

38:27.793 --> 38:28.292
Sure.

38:29.326 --> 38:31.425
You could hop on and hold on.

38:31.425 --> 38:33.758
We could go now.

38:34.525 --> 38:35.791
Oh, Jimmy I'd love to.

38:36.025 --> 38:37.091
We could come with you.

38:37.291 --> 38:39.491
I have my car, I could drive us over.

38:39.724 --> 38:41.224
Well, sure. I mean, why not?

38:41.257 --> 38:42.257
The more the merrier.

38:43.990 --> 38:44.857
Looks like tonight's

38:44.857 --> 38:46.290
going to be quite an adventure.

38:46.323 --> 38:47.057
Jimmy Flynn.

38:51.556 --> 38:52.523
After a night of fun

38:52.523 --> 38:54.622
with her new friends, the next day,

38:55.122 --> 38:56.689
a Saturday, Veronica

38:56.689 --> 38:58.022
travelled into the city to pay

38:58.022 --> 38:58.855
a visit to Cliff

38:59.722 --> 39:01.088
with a surprise for her sweetheart.

39:01.521 --> 39:03.321
She had the perfect guise to see

39:03.321 --> 39:04.721
if Cliff was a man of his word.

39:05.687 --> 39:06.754
Good morning Mrs Smart.

39:06.754 --> 39:08.420
Good to see you Mrs Smart.

39:08.420 --> 39:10.054
He's in his office Mrs Smart.

39:12.020 --> 39:15.253
Maybe I didn't make myself clear Cliff.

39:15.253 --> 39:15.786
Sweetheart.

39:15.819 --> 39:17.119
Baby, what are you doing here?

39:17.186 --> 39:18.319
Oh, I had something to

39:18.319 --> 39:19.519
attend to in the city,

39:20.086 --> 39:21.585
so I thought I'd bring you a gift.

39:22.519 --> 39:23.818
This is just work Veronica,

39:23.818 --> 39:25.485
you think I'd fool around in my office?

39:25.785 --> 39:26.618
I don't know, Cliff.

39:27.251 --> 39:28.384
I didn't expect you

39:28.384 --> 39:29.884
to fool around in our bedroom,

39:30.351 --> 39:32.417
but you proved me wrong on that one.

39:32.751 --> 39:33.217
Mrs Smart.

39:33.684 --> 39:35.484
I understand what I did was wrong,

39:35.484 --> 39:37.317
but I assure you

39:37.550 --> 39:38.950
I don't want your husband.

39:39.150 --> 39:40.416
You are acting crazy.

39:40.450 --> 39:41.483
Oh, is that so?

39:41.483 --> 39:44.682
And you are acting like a desperate fool.

39:44.849 --> 39:47.182
Did I not tell you to get rid of her?

39:47.415 --> 39:48.515
Excuse me.

39:49.482 --> 39:50.848
She's leaving at the end of the week.

39:50.915 --> 39:52.448
This is just work, Veronica.

39:52.848 --> 39:54.114
You really expect me

39:54.114 --> 39:56.014
to believe that this thing

39:56.647 --> 39:58.180
will be gone by the end of the week?

39:58.647 --> 39:59.414
That's right, Mrs.

39:59.414 --> 40:00.014
Smart.

40:00.614 --> 40:02.880
This "thing" handed in her notice today.

40:03.613 --> 40:03.880
It's

40:05.346 --> 40:06.413
true baby, Lana's an actress.

40:07.079 --> 40:07.846
She's been auditioning

40:07.846 --> 40:09.179
for new plays on Broadway.

40:09.179 --> 40:10.379
And I found out today

40:10.379 --> 40:11.645
that I got a part in the new

40:11.645 --> 40:12.812
Eugene O'Neill play.

40:12.845 --> 40:15.512
I leave in a week for two out of town

40:15.512 --> 40:17.511
tryouts, then Broadway.

40:18.611 --> 40:19.044
Baby.

40:19.678 --> 40:20.744
Isn't that exciting?

40:21.011 --> 40:21.477
Lana,

40:22.744 --> 40:24.910
I need to have a talk with my husband.

40:26.143 --> 40:27.943
Of course, Mrs Smart.

40:28.210 --> 40:29.076
Honestly, I...

40:29.076 --> 40:29.810
Out!

40:34.442 --> 40:35.642
She's, she's leaving

40:35.642 --> 40:36.709
at the end of the week,

40:36.709 --> 40:37.709
why fire the girl

40:37.709 --> 40:39.075
if she is going anyway.

40:39.775 --> 40:40.775
She's an actress?

40:42.141 --> 40:42.841
Yeah, baby.

40:43.874 --> 40:44.974
Oh, like you.

40:46.141 --> 40:47.707
Maybe she could put a word in for you.

40:48.507 --> 40:49.707
You want your mistress

40:49.707 --> 40:51.507
to put a good word in for your wife.

40:52.140 --> 40:53.906
Are you hearing yourself, Cliff?

40:53.940 --> 40:55.406
I'm just thinking of you, baby.

40:56.506 --> 40:57.673
You know, Cliff,

40:58.073 --> 40:59.139
for such a big shot,

40:59.139 --> 41:01.705
you really are stupid.

41:05.105 --> 41:06.771
You're attracted to her because.

41:07.938 --> 41:11.004
She's me 16 years ago.

41:11.037 --> 41:12.271
Baby that ain't true,

41:12.271 --> 41:13.637
she can't hold a candle to you.

41:13.637 --> 41:16.670
It is Cliff, she's living my life.

41:17.403 --> 41:19.803
She gets to be the big star

41:19.803 --> 41:22.369
while I'm stuck here teaching

41:22.369 --> 41:24.269
kids to do what I should be doing.

41:25.602 --> 41:27.069
God damn you Cliff,

41:27.469 --> 41:29.402
you really know how to hurt a lady.

41:30.735 --> 41:32.168
Well, I ain't trying to...

41:32.168 --> 41:32.801
Don't.

41:34.034 --> 41:34.801
Just don't Cliff.

41:36.334 --> 41:37.301
I hurt too much.

41:38.934 --> 41:39.200
Well,

41:40.434 --> 41:42.800
what can I do, you want me to tell her

41:42.800 --> 41:43.800
to leave right this moment

41:43.800 --> 41:44.433
because I'll do it?

41:45.233 --> 41:46.766
No, no Cliff.

41:47.866 --> 41:50.099
Let your floozy stick around,

41:50.899 --> 41:52.499
because the only thing I want.

41:53.865 --> 41:57.731
Is the last 16 years of my life back.

42:07.530 --> 42:08.297
Don't talk that way.

42:09.596 --> 42:10.963
When I was a little girl,

42:12.463 --> 42:13.662
I used to dream about what

42:13.662 --> 42:14.929
my life would be like.

42:16.495 --> 42:17.895
One thing I knew for certain.

42:19.528 --> 42:22.428
Was that I wanted to be somebody?

42:25.261 --> 42:26.494
I wanted more than

42:27.527 --> 42:30.294
those four dark, damp walls that trapped

42:30.360 --> 42:32.360
me as a child and I wanted more than

42:33.826 --> 42:35.060
my mother's loneliness

42:35.826 --> 42:36.893
and disappointment.

42:39.326 --> 42:40.626
I just knew I needed more.

42:43.492 --> 42:45.325
I would dance around in my room.

42:46.258 --> 42:48.225
Arms extended, imagining I was

42:49.158 --> 42:50.258
I was up on a stage,

42:50.258 --> 42:52.691
a vaudeville show or movie

42:52.691 --> 42:54.057
picture, I didn't care.

42:56.557 --> 42:57.890
I just knew I needed more.

42:59.923 --> 43:00.790
And then I met you.

43:03.123 --> 43:05.056
Happiest day in my whole entire life.

43:05.956 --> 43:07.189
And I thought to myself.

43:08.589 --> 43:10.088
Could this be my more

43:11.122 --> 43:13.954
to be this handsome man's wife

43:15.021 --> 43:17.321
and I thought and thought.

43:18.787 --> 43:20.087
And as much as I loved you,

43:20.087 --> 43:22.387
I knew I just couldn't

43:22.387 --> 43:23.886
give up on that part of my dream

43:25.286 --> 43:25.920
with you.

43:27.153 --> 43:28.719
You said all the right things

43:28.719 --> 43:29.752
to ease my mind.

43:32.085 --> 43:32.852
Do you remember,

43:33.818 --> 43:35.152
do you remember what you said to me

43:35.152 --> 43:36.351
when we first got together Cliff?

43:38.385 --> 43:39.584
I said I could make you happy.

43:41.584 --> 43:42.351
You said that

43:43.784 --> 43:46.517
my dreams, my ambitions

43:46.517 --> 43:48.883
would always be as important as yours,

43:49.583 --> 43:50.816
that we would help each other

43:51.349 --> 43:53.116
and support each other in it.

43:53.116 --> 43:56.116
I remember thinking perfect.

43:57.349 --> 43:58.415
Now I can be whole.

44:00.682 --> 44:03.081
But you never, never

44:03.281 --> 44:04.648
helped me or supported me,

44:04.648 --> 44:06.381
not in any way that matters,

44:07.614 --> 44:09.614
because you thought that eventually

44:10.514 --> 44:12.213
I'd give up on that part of my life.

44:13.180 --> 44:15.846
And I would just learn to be silent

44:17.413 --> 44:19.879
and just become your wife.

44:21.312 --> 44:23.512
Baby that ain't true.

44:26.345 --> 44:27.045
It is Cliff.

44:28.645 --> 44:30.178
When have you ever taken me Hollywood?

44:31.644 --> 44:32.911
I have been asking you

44:32.911 --> 44:35.610
for 16 years, but still

44:36.777 --> 44:37.843
you've never taken me.

44:38.876 --> 44:39.743
Baby, you don't need

44:39.743 --> 44:40.943
Hollywood to be a star.

44:40.976 --> 44:41.909
I know that.

44:43.009 --> 44:44.709
But I need it to make me one.

44:46.509 --> 44:48.942
Jesus, how the hell did I end up here?

44:49.942 --> 44:50.308
Now.

44:51.342 --> 44:52.475
Just stop that.

44:52.475 --> 44:54.174
This ain't a bad life

44:54.174 --> 44:55.441
you got for yourself here, Veronica.

44:55.508 --> 44:56.208
Oh, Cliff.

44:57.774 --> 44:59.807
These past few days have just confirmed

44:59.807 --> 45:01.807
everything that I already knew.

45:04.306 --> 45:06.106
You don't want me to have my more.

45:08.106 --> 45:10.639
But you sure as hell want to have yours.

45:14.738 --> 45:15.438
So that's it.

45:15.805 --> 45:17.138
We even gonna talk?

45:17.138 --> 45:17.971
Not now, Cliff.

45:18.871 --> 45:21.271
I may say something that I truly regret.

45:23.737 --> 45:24.104
Well.

45:25.704 --> 45:26.637
Will, I see you at home later?

45:28.503 --> 45:31.003
Go for a long walk after work tonight.

45:31.769 --> 45:32.936
Maybe a couple of drinks,

45:33.803 --> 45:35.536
because I really need some time

45:35.536 --> 45:38.135
to figure out what it is that I want.

45:54.966 --> 45:55.900
It ain't no mystery

45:55.900 --> 45:57.399
that the youths who live in the slum

45:57.399 --> 45:58.899
side of town lived a life of risk.

45:59.666 --> 46:00.799
Some of the kids like Riff

46:00.799 --> 46:01.999
didn't live with their parents.

46:02.232 --> 46:03.165
For them it is the street.

46:03.832 --> 46:04.532
Some have to work

46:04.532 --> 46:05.532
their fingers to the bone,

46:05.765 --> 46:07.731
sacrificing an education to pitch in.

46:08.365 --> 46:09.798
Sure, the boys had a few run

46:09.798 --> 46:11.031
ins with the law, but

46:11.031 --> 46:12.264
it was petty stuff, mainly

46:12.464 --> 46:14.197
just to put a hot meal inside them.

46:14.630 --> 46:15.730
But these were good kids,

46:16.230 --> 46:17.997
living in surroundings that could easily

46:17.997 --> 46:19.196
take them down the wrong path.

46:20.196 --> 46:21.729
That night, Jimmy

46:21.729 --> 46:22.996
joined Riff by the Docks,

46:23.696 --> 46:24.696
a regular hangout

46:25.262 --> 46:27.095
for the undesirables of the city.

46:36.328 --> 46:37.261
So what you get?

46:37.961 --> 46:39.160
Two bucks and a coupon

46:39.327 --> 46:40.927
for canned meat.

46:40.927 --> 46:42.793
Damn it Jimmy, I can't keep doing this.

46:42.793 --> 46:43.360
Doing what?

46:43.360 --> 46:44.426
Pickpocketing, breaking

46:44.426 --> 46:45.393
into people's houses.

46:45.493 --> 46:46.759
Well you know what to do Riff.

46:46.759 --> 46:48.626
I can't stay with you.

46:49.059 --> 46:50.492
I ain't going to be a burden to nobody.

46:50.759 --> 46:51.792
Riff you ain't no burden,

46:52.659 --> 46:53.559
your my best friend.

46:53.592 --> 46:54.892
I want to help.

46:54.892 --> 46:55.625
Jimmy, your old man can

46:55.625 --> 46:56.725
barely afford to keep you,

46:56.725 --> 46:57.391
he ain't looking for

46:57.391 --> 46:58.658
no new kid in the house.

47:01.957 --> 47:03.891
I gotta have a future Jimmy, I just gotta.

47:03.891 --> 47:05.457
This can't be it.

47:05.457 --> 47:07.123
I know just how you feel Riff, but.

47:08.590 --> 47:10.456
Well, that's a problem for another day.

47:10.723 --> 47:13.489
No, it ain't, we're sixteen now Jimmy

47:13.489 --> 47:14.889
there's a whole world

47:14.889 --> 47:16.389
out there, opportunities you know.

47:16.389 --> 47:18.155
Sure thing Riff, but that's a whole world

47:18.155 --> 47:19.588
you and I ain't ever going to see.

47:19.588 --> 47:20.922
Don't say that.

47:28.954 --> 47:29.787
It's been one year

47:29.954 --> 47:31.287
since my parents die.

47:34.320 --> 47:35.053
Jeez.

47:38.386 --> 47:39.452
I didn't even realise.

47:42.685 --> 47:43.352
I'm sorry.

47:45.252 --> 47:46.518
One year since the fire.

47:49.418 --> 47:51.251
God, that one moment in my life

47:51.251 --> 47:53.051
and I lost everything.

47:56.417 --> 47:56.917
You know.

47:59.416 --> 48:00.483
You are my family.

48:01.050 --> 48:01.683
I know.

48:01.949 --> 48:03.149
I mean, it is great.

48:03.149 --> 48:05.882
But I mean, it's not the same.

48:05.882 --> 48:10.682
After seeing Veronicas house

48:10.682 --> 48:12.048
I got this aching feeling all over me.

48:13.215 --> 48:14.215
What do you mean?

48:14.514 --> 48:15.114
I got jealous?

48:16.081 --> 48:17.881
All that money, the house,

48:17.881 --> 48:19.447
all those rooms.

48:19.447 --> 48:22.380
My house burns to the ground,

48:22.380 --> 48:24.413
taking my parents with it and here I am.

48:26.513 --> 48:27.846
When did we get chosen

48:27.846 --> 48:28.946
to be the failures?

48:29.946 --> 48:31.246
We ain't living in a world

48:31.246 --> 48:32.612
that wants to hear what we got to say.

48:32.612 --> 48:34.845
You know, people would rather

48:34.845 --> 48:37.045
just walk past us, pretend we don't exist.

48:37.045 --> 48:38.811
Why does it have to be final?

48:39.211 --> 48:41.144
People must find a way out of this.

48:41.311 --> 48:42.444
I mean, Jesus Jimmy,

48:42.544 --> 48:44.144
my shoes are falling apart,

48:44.144 --> 48:45.110
I haven't slept well

48:45.110 --> 48:46.110
in a year, and I'm hungry.

48:46.710 --> 48:48.543
I'm hungry all the time.

48:48.543 --> 48:50.210
The only time I get to eat is at school.

48:51.510 --> 48:52.976
Whatever happened to the American dream?

48:54.076 --> 48:55.942
The thing with the American dream is

48:56.509 --> 48:58.275
most of us wake up.

48:59.475 --> 49:00.408
We move on.

49:00.442 --> 49:01.975
Not everyone can be a success.

49:01.975 --> 49:02.641
No.

49:03.008 --> 49:04.208
Riff the streets are paved

49:04.208 --> 49:05.074
with shit and poverty.

49:06.208 --> 49:09.007
The gold, It's rare.

49:10.007 --> 49:11.674
Now, we may never get the gold,

49:11.674 --> 49:12.473
but we just got to avoid

49:12.473 --> 49:13.307
the shit, you know.

49:13.607 --> 49:15.506
So what, I just sit here

49:15.506 --> 49:16.206
and hope some shlep

49:16.206 --> 49:18.506
gives me a dime or two?

49:18.506 --> 49:19.639
God bless America.

49:19.639 --> 49:21.639
I can grab you something from my house.

49:23.172 --> 49:23.705
Or I could.

49:25.772 --> 49:26.205
Help.

49:27.805 --> 49:28.471
You know.

49:28.738 --> 49:29.838
If I gotta take something

49:29.838 --> 49:31.371
heavy on, I'm doing it alone.

49:32.104 --> 49:33.437
I'm fine, really Jimmy.

49:33.971 --> 49:37.470
You just go home, I'll see you tomorrow.

49:37.470 --> 49:38.337
I promise.

49:43.436 --> 49:43.936
Alright.

49:48.802 --> 49:49.435
You be careful out here,

49:49.569 --> 49:50.335
you hear me.

49:53.268 --> 49:55.534
Jimmy leaves Riff on the docks,

49:55.534 --> 49:57.901
but as Riff follows him away

49:57.901 --> 49:59.967
See you tomorrow Riff.

50:01.167 --> 50:03.333
He sees a man walking down the docks.

50:03.333 --> 50:05.100
Alone.

50:06.066 --> 50:08.199
You need to eat Riff.

50:08.199 --> 50:09.566
But as the figure gets closer.

50:10.366 --> 50:11.266
Well, how could he know?

50:12.199 --> 50:13.699
How could he have known the man

50:13.699 --> 50:15.265
approaching was Cliff Smart,

50:16.265 --> 50:17.498
wandering the streets,

50:17.998 --> 50:20.264
thinking about his failures as a husband?

50:24.864 --> 50:25.997
Hey, step aside.

50:26.430 --> 50:27.430
Not so fast, mister.

50:27.463 --> 50:28.663
I'm going to need ten,

50:28.730 --> 50:30.996
I mean five bucks for you to pass.

50:30.996 --> 50:32.696
A tax, if you will.

50:32.963 --> 50:34.163
I said, get out of my way.

50:34.163 --> 50:35.129
I ain't in the mood.

50:35.129 --> 50:36.662
I ain't gonna ask you again.

50:37.629 --> 50:38.195
Look at

50:38.795 --> 50:40.295
you ain't getting anything from me.

50:41.062 --> 50:41.862
So why don't you run

50:41.862 --> 50:43.095
on home to mommy and daddy

50:43.095 --> 50:44.761
so they can teach you some respect?

50:44.794 --> 50:45.461
What did you say?

50:46.728 --> 50:47.727
I said move.

50:49.127 --> 50:51.260
I just need some money for some food...

50:51.260 --> 50:52.927
Ain't interested in your sob story, kid.

50:54.127 --> 50:54.760
Jesus.

50:55.693 --> 50:57.493
Your parents sure as hell failed you.

51:00.759 --> 51:02.425
Oh, you are dead!

51:09.125 --> 51:11.124
I just wanted to eat,

51:11.124 --> 51:12.024
why couldn't you see,

51:12.024 --> 51:13.224
I just wanted to eat,

51:14.324 --> 51:15.924
I ain't a bad kid, I swear.

51:17.690 --> 51:18.557
I'm sorry, Mr.

51:19.423 --> 51:20.123
I'm sorry.

51:28.622 --> 51:30.122
Cliff.

51:30.122 --> 51:31.588
What happened to you, are you ok?

51:31.855 --> 51:34.621
Sure, act like you care, Veronica.

51:34.954 --> 51:36.221
What a cold thing to say.

51:36.521 --> 51:37.887
I ain't in the mood to argue.

51:37.921 --> 51:38.387
Come here.

51:38.621 --> 51:39.321
Let me see it.

51:47.153 --> 51:48.553
Oh, that looks like a nasty gash,

51:48.553 --> 51:50.052
I think we're going to have to call

51:50.052 --> 51:52.219
Dr. Morgan out just to be safe.

51:52.885 --> 51:54.085
I don't need that quack.

51:55.085 --> 51:56.085
I'll be fine as soon

51:56.085 --> 51:58.151
as my head stops spinning.

51:58.151 --> 51:58.551
Well,

51:59.585 --> 52:00.451
what happened to you?

52:00.618 --> 52:02.118
It looks as though you were attacked.

52:03.584 --> 52:05.084
I took a walk after work

52:05.084 --> 52:06.817
down by the waterfront.

52:07.683 --> 52:08.717
I went down through the tunnel

52:08.717 --> 52:10.450
where the street kids live.

52:11.450 --> 52:12.583
One of them hit me with a bat

52:12.583 --> 52:13.483
and took my money,

52:14.283 --> 52:15.282
son of a bitch.

52:16.082 --> 52:17.915
If I ever lay my eyes on him again, then.

52:18.982 --> 52:20.582
He ain't going to see his next birthday.

52:20.882 --> 52:22.115
Why would you go down there?

52:22.748 --> 52:24.248
I was trying to clear my mind.

52:24.815 --> 52:26.148
You told me to take a walk.

52:26.448 --> 52:27.281
You needed time.

52:27.514 --> 52:28.414
But down there.

52:30.314 --> 52:31.380
The police should take out

52:31.380 --> 52:33.680
a gun and get rid of the vermin

52:33.680 --> 52:35.413
who do nothing but dirty up the city.

52:36.213 --> 52:37.679
Cliff, most of them are children

52:37.679 --> 52:39.346
who have fallen on hard times.

52:39.379 --> 52:40.612
Not everybody was

52:40.612 --> 52:42.079
as privileged as you were.

52:42.712 --> 52:44.879
Wait, your defending them?

52:45.545 --> 52:46.945
No, no.

52:46.945 --> 52:47.611
It's just.

52:48.545 --> 52:50.744
Some of the kids I teach live down there,

52:51.311 --> 52:53.344
you know, school is all they have

52:53.344 --> 52:55.144
at given them any kind of a shot.

52:56.477 --> 52:57.710
I just feel sorry for them.

52:58.877 --> 53:00.076
Well they ain't getting a shot.

53:00.943 --> 53:01.743
God don't pay no

53:01.743 --> 53:02.876
attention to those kinds.

53:03.676 --> 53:05.509
You really can be so cruel.

53:06.009 --> 53:07.842
Hey, it's my head split open here.

53:09.709 --> 53:13.075
So these boys, what do they look like?

53:14.108 --> 53:15.108
All these street kids

53:15.108 --> 53:15.941
look the same to me,

53:17.108 --> 53:19.374
although I do know

53:19.374 --> 53:20.607
that one of them was called Riff.

53:21.907 --> 53:23.640
Riff? Yeah.

53:24.807 --> 53:26.306
One of his friends shouted at him,

53:27.073 --> 53:29.539
slipped up and used his name.

53:29.539 --> 53:30.906
Degenerates.

53:30.906 --> 53:31.839
He could have killed you.

53:44.171 --> 53:45.170
Some say that the kids

53:45.170 --> 53:46.237
never stood a chance.

53:46.837 --> 53:47.837
They were broken,

53:48.303 --> 53:50.503
searching for something more and easily

53:50.503 --> 53:51.736
manipulated by a woman

53:51.736 --> 53:52.936
who took advantage of it all.

53:53.869 --> 53:55.869
I say, I guess that's for you to decide.

53:55.869 --> 53:57.369
But one thing is undeniable.

53:57.902 --> 54:00.202
She certainly shook things up all right

54:00.202 --> 54:01.602
and she spun a web

54:01.602 --> 54:02.968
that a vulnerable person could

54:02.968 --> 54:04.035
easily fall into.

54:04.701 --> 54:05.801
And Vivian, did.

54:06.701 --> 54:08.201
You have been out after school

54:08.201 --> 54:09.234
every evening this week,

54:09.234 --> 54:10.367
where are you going?

54:10.500 --> 54:11.534
I am not telling you mother,

54:11.534 --> 54:12.933
because you'll only judge.

54:13.200 --> 54:13.600
Fine.

54:13.967 --> 54:14.667
Then you won't be leaving

54:14.800 --> 54:15.566
this house tonight.

54:15.566 --> 54:16.300
Vivian Pierce.

54:16.833 --> 54:18.133
I am not a child anymore.

54:18.166 --> 54:19.166
I'm fifteen.

54:19.199 --> 54:20.966
A child is exactly what you are.

54:22.965 --> 54:24.499
You're out with those boys again.

54:24.532 --> 54:25.898
Do you think I don't know that

54:26.365 --> 54:28.198
you can't outsmart your mother.

54:28.331 --> 54:28.765
Ha!

54:29.398 --> 54:30.031
Then you're wrong.

54:30.031 --> 54:30.698
Vivian!

54:30.864 --> 54:31.698
I've been going to see

54:31.698 --> 54:33.197
my new teacher, actually.

54:33.731 --> 54:34.797
Mrs Smart?

54:34.931 --> 54:35.764
The lady I met?

54:35.830 --> 54:36.330
Yes.

54:36.597 --> 54:37.897
She's been teaching me all about

54:37.897 --> 54:38.997
how to make it in Hollywood.

54:39.163 --> 54:41.030
Private lessons for free.

54:41.363 --> 54:41.963
Oh, mother.

54:41.963 --> 54:43.296
She's one of the most fascinating

54:43.296 --> 54:44.429
people I've ever met.

54:44.929 --> 54:46.429
Acting, no.

54:47.362 --> 54:47.995
But mother, it's

54:47.995 --> 54:50.062
something I want so bad that it hurts.

54:50.728 --> 54:51.828
Oh, Vivian,

54:52.128 --> 54:54.061
you are not going to be a movie star.

54:54.295 --> 54:55.961
You are far too plain looking.

54:56.061 --> 54:57.661
No, no, I'm not,

54:57.661 --> 54:58.861
I've got great bone structure.

54:59.061 --> 55:00.227
Veronica told me.

55:00.927 --> 55:01.894
I don't know what's going on

55:01.894 --> 55:03.527
with you, Vivian, but I don't like it.

55:03.527 --> 55:05.027
Why can't you just be happy?

55:05.127 --> 55:06.593
Because I've lived Vivian.

55:06.593 --> 55:07.826
I know the dangers

55:07.826 --> 55:09.459
and I want to protect you.

55:09.493 --> 55:10.692
I am going, mother.

55:11.892 --> 55:13.425
It's a scary world out there.

55:14.392 --> 55:15.625
And people's motives aren't always

55:15.625 --> 55:16.658
what they appear to be.

55:19.658 --> 55:21.158
Living with that fear

55:21.791 --> 55:23.391
is not living, mother.

55:25.024 --> 55:25.291
Now.

55:26.824 --> 55:27.824
I'll be home by ten.

55:29.323 --> 55:29.990
Don't wait up.

55:46.254 --> 55:48.587
My dad doesn't show love.

55:50.121 --> 55:50.854
He hates me.

55:51.020 --> 55:51.454
No.

55:51.454 --> 55:52.087
It's cool.

55:53.253 --> 55:54.353
Sometimes you're not supposed

55:54.353 --> 55:55.287
to like your parents

55:56.053 --> 55:58.419
or they're not supposed to like you,

55:58.419 --> 55:59.119
I guess.

55:59.986 --> 56:00.786
