I ain't going to say anything,

1:33:12.089 --> 1:33:13.755
but I can not be involved,

1:33:13.755 --> 1:33:16.088
and I pray you don't go through this

1:33:16.955 --> 1:33:17.688
Riff, wait.

1:33:19.288 --> 1:33:20.421
What, Jimmy?

1:33:21.621 --> 1:33:23.353
I need your gun.

1:33:24.254 --> 1:33:25.421
If you ain't gonna help,

1:33:25.421 --> 1:33:26.887
you can at least do that.

1:33:27.120 --> 1:33:28.219
I ain't got it on me.

1:33:28.353 --> 1:33:29.387
I let a friend borrow it.

1:33:29.387 --> 1:33:29.719
Riff.

1:33:30.487 --> 1:33:32.253
Damn you Jimmy Flynn for telling me this.

1:33:34.719 --> 1:33:35.386
Fine.

1:33:36.318 --> 1:33:37.786
The night you're going to do the deed

1:33:38.085 --> 1:33:39.552
I'll meet you before

1:33:39.552 --> 1:33:41.018
and let you borrow it.

1:33:44.684 --> 1:33:45.751
Thank you.

1:33:47.518 --> 1:33:49.484
You know, you really are my best friend.

1:33:49.651 --> 1:33:51.050
Whatever you say Jimmy.

1:33:51.117 --> 1:33:51.784
I got to go.

1:33:52.584 --> 1:33:53.650
My future is calling.

1:33:55.782 --> 1:33:56.883
They say the road to hell

1:33:56.883 --> 1:33:58.349
is paved with good intentions,

1:33:58.349 --> 1:34:00.683
and maybe that's the best way to describe

1:34:00.683 --> 1:34:01.482
Jimmy's decision.

1:34:02.116 --> 1:34:04.715
Cliff was now a dead man walking.

1:34:04.715 --> 1:34:07.682
That night, out clearing his head,

1:34:07.682 --> 1:34:09.548
Cliff stops dead in his tracks

1:34:09.548 --> 1:34:11.114
when he sees Riff in front of him

1:34:11.114 --> 1:34:12.148
warming his hands.

1:34:15.114 --> 1:34:15.647
You!

1:34:15.781 --> 1:34:18.680
After a moment Riff's eyes lock on Cliff.

1:34:19.480 --> 1:34:20.447
It was like a showdown

1:34:20.447 --> 1:34:21.380
from the Wild West.

1:34:22.013 --> 1:34:23.280
But who would flinch first?

1:34:23.513 --> 1:34:25.779
We still have unfinished business, kid.

1:34:26.279 --> 1:34:27.079
Mr. Smart.

1:34:41.677 --> 1:34:42.943
It's so different.

1:34:43.344 --> 1:34:44.277
You look...

1:34:44.543 --> 1:34:45.210
Glamorous?

1:34:45.710 --> 1:34:46.510
Older.

1:34:46.843 --> 1:34:47.843
Well, good.

1:34:48.143 --> 1:34:49.243
Hopefully people start

1:34:49.243 --> 1:34:50.376
to see me as a grown-up

1:34:50.376 --> 1:34:51.876
rather than some dumb kid.

1:34:52.709 --> 1:34:54.575
Has your mother see your transformation?

1:34:55.509 --> 1:34:57.075
Oh, she's out.

1:34:57.608 --> 1:34:58.875
She'll see it when she gets back.

1:34:58.907 --> 1:35:00.108
I'm sure she'll think it's fine.

1:35:01.008 --> 1:35:02.708
Have you met your mother?

1:35:02.708 --> 1:35:03.741
And Vivian,

1:35:03.741 --> 1:35:05.907
how did you manage to afford this?

1:35:05.941 --> 1:35:08.607
Oh, Veronica paid, she said,

1:35:08.607 --> 1:35:11.340
I remind her of her when she was my age.

1:35:11.673 --> 1:35:12.573
She's always getting me

1:35:12.573 --> 1:35:14.106
little gifts we're even talking

1:35:14.106 --> 1:35:15.773
about going to Hollywood together.

1:35:16.239 --> 1:35:17.206
Hollywood?

1:35:17.206 --> 1:35:18.139
Vivian,

1:35:18.306 --> 1:35:20.239
your mother nearly has heart failure

1:35:20.239 --> 1:35:21.705
every time we go camping,

1:35:22.038 --> 1:35:24.271
and that's usually in your backyard.

1:35:25.438 --> 1:35:27.004
Do you think I should go blond?

1:35:27.603 --> 1:35:29.704
I mean, Veronica says the dark suits me,

1:35:29.704 --> 1:35:31.537
but I'm not so sure.

1:35:31.537 --> 1:35:32.670
You do realise that

1:35:32.670 --> 1:35:33.937
all that comes out your mouth now

1:35:33.937 --> 1:35:35.570
is about Jimmy's new girlfriend.

1:35:35.603 --> 1:35:36.969
Girlfriend is a stretch Betty.

1:35:38.103 --> 1:35:39.702
He's just some teenage crush.

1:35:40.303 --> 1:35:41.269
Veronica and I,

1:35:41.568 --> 1:35:43.036
we have a true connection, like

1:35:43.402 --> 1:35:44.769
on a deeper level, you know.

1:35:45.602 --> 1:35:46.535
Not really.

1:35:46.668 --> 1:35:48.168
Plus, it's nice to have grown up

1:35:48.168 --> 1:35:49.501
conversations for a change.

1:35:51.234 --> 1:35:53.168
So what am I just some dumb kid?

1:35:53.300 --> 1:35:55.367
No, you're just different.

1:35:55.800 --> 1:35:57.834
What we have is our thing and what I have

1:35:57.834 --> 1:35:59.333
with Veronica, is...

1:36:00.000 --> 1:36:00.733
Better?

1:36:00.733 --> 1:36:01.500
Betty.

1:36:01.900 --> 1:36:03.532
You promised that I wouldn't be

1:36:03.532 --> 1:36:05.499
replaced by your new glamorous friend,

1:36:05.799 --> 1:36:07.799
but I hardly see you anymore.

1:36:07.832 --> 1:36:09.332
Why aren't you happy for me?

1:36:09.599 --> 1:36:10.565
You know what, you're supposed

1:36:10.565 --> 1:36:12.032
to be my best friend.

1:36:12.032 --> 1:36:13.165
When it suits you.

1:36:13.165 --> 1:36:15.531
I'm changing Betty and you better get

1:36:15.531 --> 1:36:16.264
used to it or sit down

1:36:16.264 --> 1:36:17.731
and stay the hell out of my way.

1:36:18.098 --> 1:36:19.231
Goodbye, Vivian.

1:36:20.231 --> 1:36:21.630
I know when I'm not wanted.

1:36:22.697 --> 1:36:24.063
I just didn't think it would be you

1:36:24.063 --> 1:36:25.630
that didnt want me.

1:36:26.263 --> 1:36:27.830
Betty!

1:36:28.896 --> 1:36:30.129
Betty?

1:36:33.262 --> 1:36:34.495
Kids.

1:36:39.327 --> 1:36:41.827
My name? Oh,

1:36:43.561 --> 1:36:46.127
it's Vivian, Vivian Pierce.

1:36:46.527 --> 1:36:47.760
It's a pleasure to meet you.

1:36:48.260 --> 1:36:50.027
Did I tell you that I was an actress?

1:36:50.927 --> 1:36:54.093
Yes, I've starred in several movies.

1:36:54.259 --> 1:36:56.526
Actually, one critic

1:36:57.026 --> 1:37:01.025
even called me "dazzling".

1:37:04.425 --> 1:37:06.225
What on earth have you done to yourself?

1:37:06.491 --> 1:37:06.991
Mother?

1:37:08.058 --> 1:37:09.757
Take that stuff off your face.

1:37:10.291 --> 1:37:11.291
You think going to church

1:37:11.291 --> 1:37:12.389
looking like some teenage

1:37:12.389 --> 1:37:13.823
Jezebel is appropriate?

1:37:14.123 --> 1:37:15.223
It's just make up mother

1:37:15.223 --> 1:37:16.123
and a new hairdo.

1:37:16.257 --> 1:37:18.090
Why did you have to be such a drag?

1:37:18.090 --> 1:37:19.723
And I'm not coming to church.

1:37:20.255 --> 1:37:21.323
I feel like you're changing right

1:37:21.323 --> 1:37:21.989
in front of my eyes

1:37:21.989 --> 1:37:23.056
and I can't reach you.

1:37:23.556 --> 1:37:24.489
I keep trying but

1:37:24.489 --> 1:37:25.822
you keep pushing me away.

1:37:25.922 --> 1:37:27.955
You need to stop worrying about me.

1:37:28.388 --> 1:37:29.888
You've done your job, mother.

1:37:30.388 --> 1:37:32.088
Now it's time for me to take over.

1:37:32.154 --> 1:37:33.487
Vivian, I think it's time

1:37:33.487 --> 1:37:34.687
I put my foot down.

1:37:34.687 --> 1:37:36.487
You would have to take it off my throat

1:37:36.787 --> 1:37:37.954
first mother.

1:37:37.987 --> 1:37:39.053
You listen to me.

1:37:39.120 --> 1:37:41.053
No, you listen to me.

1:37:41.620 --> 1:37:42.786
This constant need

1:37:42.786 --> 1:37:46.619
to turn me into you is nauseating mother.

1:37:47.219 --> 1:37:49.352
I don't want to be Vivian Pierce.

1:37:49.619 --> 1:37:51.385
There's nothing wrong with her.

1:37:51.418 --> 1:37:54.218
She's so black and white.

1:37:54.518 --> 1:37:55.985
I want to see the world in color.

1:37:56.085 --> 1:37:57.418
I wan to be like those ladies

1:37:57.451 --> 1:37:58.751
who can just click their fingers

1:37:58.751 --> 1:38:00.084
and get whatever they want.

1:38:00.251 --> 1:38:01.617
Well, that is not the real world Vivian.

1:38:01.884 --> 1:38:04.183
No, that is not your world, mother.

1:38:07.216 --> 1:38:08.216
Look at you.

1:38:08.850 --> 1:38:11.282
You give up the day you got married.

1:38:11.882 --> 1:38:13.249
Vivian, your father will...

1:38:13.249 --> 1:38:13.716
What?

1:38:14.815 --> 1:38:16.548
Go ahead and call my father.

1:38:16.582 --> 1:38:17.982
I'm not scared of him.

1:38:19.948 --> 1:38:21.781
You know, you can't think

1:38:22.081 --> 1:38:24.314
without a man telling you what to do.

1:38:24.914 --> 1:38:26.847
If it's not father, it's God.

1:38:31.913 --> 1:38:33.013
Is this because of that woman?

1:38:34.978 --> 1:38:36.112
I've seen her around town,

1:38:36.112 --> 1:38:37.579
you know, your actress friend.

1:38:38.312 --> 1:38:39.679
Flashy is not attractive

1:38:39.679 --> 1:38:40.679
on a woman her age.

1:38:40.679 --> 1:38:42.378
And jealousy is not attractive

1:38:42.378 --> 1:38:43.612
and a woman of your age.

1:38:44.611 --> 1:38:45.545
Give me that dress.

1:38:46.011 --> 1:38:46.844
Give it back mother.

1:38:46.844 --> 1:38:48.644
This is not you Vivian.

1:38:48.644 --> 1:38:49.344
Give it back now.

1:38:49.344 --> 1:38:51.210
What has gotten into you?

1:38:55.843 --> 1:38:59.675
Keep your hands off of my things, Jean.

1:39:01.609 --> 1:39:02.609
Please respect that.

1:39:10.508 --> 1:39:11.641
Vivian.

1:39:13.641 --> 1:39:14.741
You don't need to be

1:39:14.741 --> 1:39:16.041
in such a rush to grow up.

1:39:19.507 --> 1:39:21.840
The world is not always kind to women.

1:39:24.106 --> 1:39:25.439
Do you think I didn't have dreams?

1:39:28.306 --> 1:39:30.005
I wanted to open my own sewing shop.

1:39:31.005 --> 1:39:33.138
Atlantic City, near the boardwalk

1:39:34.438 --> 1:39:36.904
that's where I dreamed of opening it.

1:39:39.304 --> 1:39:41.037
But life isn't a dream Vivian,

1:39:42.937 --> 1:39:43.837
do you think this lady

1:39:43.837 --> 1:39:45.137
is going to turn you into a star?

1:39:45.503 --> 1:39:46.503
She's not.

1:39:48.070 --> 1:39:50.103
That doesn't happen for girls like you.

1:39:54.136 --> 1:39:55.835
You gave up your dream

1:39:57.535 --> 1:39:59.568
because you're weak.

1:40:13.800 --> 1:40:14.933
Good morning, sweetheart.

1:40:15.966 --> 1:40:16.799
What's all this?

1:40:17.332 --> 1:40:17.866
Breakfast.

1:40:18.699 --> 1:40:20.264
You know, now we've got our own

1:40:20.264 --> 1:40:21.565
little bundle of joy on the way.

1:40:21.565 --> 1:40:22.998
I thought I ought to learn to do

1:40:22.998 --> 1:40:24.032
my part around here.

1:40:24.665 --> 1:40:26.365
Well, crazier things have happened,

1:40:26.365 --> 1:40:27.098
I suppose.

1:40:31.231 --> 1:40:31.996
I told my mother.

1:40:32.364 --> 1:40:33.496
You told your mother?

1:40:33.664 --> 1:40:34.496
I couldn't wait.

1:40:34.496 --> 1:40:35.697
It was bursting out of me.

1:40:35.730 --> 1:40:38.263
I specifically told you not to tell her.

1:40:38.763 --> 1:40:39.829
It's still early.

1:40:40.263 --> 1:40:41.129
And as you pointed out,

1:40:41.129 --> 1:40:42.496
I'm an old shrew now.

1:40:42.496 --> 1:40:45.495
So this is clearly a delicate pregnancy.

1:40:45.862 --> 1:40:47.628
Well, I never called you a shrew.

1:40:48.628 --> 1:40:49.262
Coffee?

1:40:49.861 --> 1:40:50.528
Thank you.

1:40:51.327 --> 1:40:53.994
Now, Cliff, please don't go

1:40:53.994 --> 1:40:56.027
sharing our news with anybody else,

1:40:56.294 --> 1:40:57.527
especially the boys at work.

1:40:57.994 --> 1:40:59.559
Don't think I don't know you can out

1:40:59.559 --> 1:41:00.993
gossip the ladies at the markets.

1:41:01.693 --> 1:41:03.126
I swear on all the Saints.

1:41:04.425 --> 1:41:06.826
I can't tell you how excited I am.

1:41:07.826 --> 1:41:09.059
I can't sleep anymore

1:41:09.059 --> 1:41:10.459
knowing that the day I dreamt

1:41:10.459 --> 1:41:12.692
about is so close.

1:41:12.692 --> 1:41:14.225
It's a new start.

1:41:15.291 --> 1:41:16.891
We still have time, Cliff.

1:41:17.191 --> 1:41:19.624
Let's not go wasting all of our joy.

1:41:19.991 --> 1:41:21.557
We'll have none left for the child.

1:41:25.557 --> 1:41:29.023
You um, you are

1:41:29.689 --> 1:41:32.289
excited about our baby aren't you?

1:41:32.289 --> 1:41:33.621
I can hardly wait.

1:41:33.922 --> 1:41:35.389
That's what I needed to hear.

1:41:36.589 --> 1:41:36.987
Now,

1:41:38.355 --> 1:41:39.621
do you need anything else before I go?

1:41:40.987 --> 1:41:42.621
Cliff I'm not even showing yet.

1:41:43.321 --> 1:41:44.821
I think I'm perfectly capable

1:41:44.821 --> 1:41:46.021
of looking after myself

1:41:46.021 --> 1:41:46.987
whilst you're at work.

1:41:47.487 --> 1:41:49.054
After all, I have done it

1:41:49.054 --> 1:41:50.420
for the past 16 years.

1:41:51.387 --> 1:41:52.053
OK, baby.

1:41:54.186 --> 1:41:55.318
Have a good day, Cliff.

1:41:55.886 --> 1:41:56.653
Oh, and

1:41:57.919 --> 1:41:58.486
Veronica.

1:41:59.485 --> 1:42:00.619
Yes, Cliff.

1:42:01.885 --> 1:42:03.152
You are starting to show a little.

1:42:06.118 --> 1:42:07.451
It's beautiful.

1:42:08.550 --> 1:42:09.284
What?

1:42:10.317 --> 1:42:11.017
Bye baby.

1:42:18.083 --> 1:42:19.816
The moment Cliff left the room,

1:42:19.816 --> 1:42:21.216
Veronica jumps up

1:42:21.216 --> 1:42:22.148
and heads for the phone.

1:42:24.849 --> 1:42:27.282
Operator, connect me to New York,

1:42:27.282 --> 1:42:28.682
seven, three, two, four please.

1:42:29.348 --> 1:42:29.815
Thank you.

1:42:32.648 --> 1:42:33.248
Is that you?

1:42:34.148 --> 1:42:35.880
Oh, Jimmy, we have to do this soon.

1:42:36.347 --> 1:42:38.114
His temper is out of control.

1:42:38.414 --> 1:42:39.847
My face still stings.

1:42:40.013 --> 1:42:41.580
He ain't ever going to learn is he?

1:42:42.513 --> 1:42:44.446
He's just bad, bad to the core.

1:42:44.913 --> 1:42:47.812
Oh, Jimmy, Jimmy, I am scared.

1:42:48.379 --> 1:42:50.412
I'm scared for the life of our baby.

1:42:51.279 --> 1:42:51.912
Don't worry.

1:42:53.512 --> 1:42:54.612
I'm ready when you are.

1:42:55.011 --> 1:42:55.745
Oh, Jimmy.

1:42:56.645 --> 1:42:58.978
Every time I hear your voice, it's

1:42:59.378 --> 1:43:01.044
like the rain clouds lifting.

1:43:01.844 --> 1:43:02.977
I can see clearly,

1:43:03.577 --> 1:43:06.110
I can see our future so clearly.

1:43:07.010 --> 1:43:08.076
When should we do this?

1:43:08.910 --> 1:43:10.009
Tomorrow night, Jimmy.

1:43:10.709 --> 1:43:12.409
We have to do this tomorrow night.

1:43:13.342 --> 1:43:14.309
Tell me you love me.

1:43:16.209 --> 1:43:17.808
Jimmy, I gotta go.

1:43:24.907 --> 1:43:26.807
Vivian, well, don't

1:43:26.807 --> 1:43:28.240
you look like a knockout?

1:43:28.574 --> 1:43:30.073
I knew that dress would suit you.

1:43:30.639 --> 1:43:32.073
Oh, thank you Veronica.

1:43:32.073 --> 1:43:33.406
You look beautiful, too.

1:43:33.973 --> 1:43:34.505
Why thank you.

1:43:35.139 --> 1:43:36.673
Now Vivian, what are you doing here?

1:43:36.906 --> 1:43:38.172
Not that I'm not delighted

1:43:38.172 --> 1:43:39.339
for your visit, of course.

1:43:39.572 --> 1:43:40.672
Well, since we didn't

1:43:40.672 --> 1:43:41.839
meet this week after school,

1:43:41.839 --> 1:43:44.038
I thought I'd stop by and say hello.

1:43:44.605 --> 1:43:45.805
That's what friends do, isn't it?

1:43:46.071 --> 1:43:48.171
They pop by and say hello.

1:43:48.638 --> 1:43:50.404
And we are friends, aren't we, Veronica?

1:43:50.937 --> 1:43:52.637
Of course Vivian.

1:43:53.969 --> 1:43:57.103
In fact, I'm delighted you stopped by.

1:43:57.403 --> 1:43:58.070
Really?

1:43:58.070 --> 1:43:58.736
Sure.

1:43:59.236 --> 1:44:00.903
I mean, I think it's about time

1:44:00.903 --> 1:44:02.436
we had another acting lesson.

1:44:02.536 --> 1:44:05.434
Only this time let's do it away from here

1:44:05.434 --> 1:44:06.702
or or the school.

1:44:07.002 --> 1:44:08.102
Let's make it more like

1:44:08.502 --> 1:44:10.501
two girls out on the town.

1:44:10.800 --> 1:44:11.601
Oh, Mrs. Smart.

1:44:11.635 --> 1:44:12.634
I would love that.

1:44:13.034 --> 1:44:14.867
We could go to a bar and well,

1:44:14.901 --> 1:44:16.101
I could teach you all about

1:44:16.101 --> 1:44:18.034
how to audition for a movie picture.

1:44:18.500 --> 1:44:19.434
A drink?

1:44:19.933 --> 1:44:20.733
In a bar?

1:44:21.000 --> 1:44:21.600
Sure.

1:44:21.867 --> 1:44:22.866
Oh, Mrs. Smart.

1:44:23.233 --> 1:44:24.333
I would love that.

1:44:24.333 --> 1:44:26.199
But I'm only fifteen.

1:44:26.733 --> 1:44:28.532
But in this dress, Vivian,

1:44:28.532 --> 1:44:30.932
you look like a beautiful woman.

1:44:31.332 --> 1:44:32.398
Every bar in town

1:44:32.398 --> 1:44:33.065
will want you to light

1:44:33.065 --> 1:44:35.565
up their establishment and it'll be nice.

1:44:36.065 --> 1:44:37.198
Just us girls.

1:44:38.164 --> 1:44:41.397
Just us girls?

1:44:41.397 --> 1:44:41.831
You and I?

1:44:41.831 --> 1:44:44.564
A sweet gesture, a blossoming friendship.

1:44:45.330 --> 1:44:47.830
No, Veronica was lining up

1:44:47.830 --> 1:44:49.663
alibis like a professional crook.

1:44:50.362 --> 1:44:51.963
Poor sweet Vivian

1:44:51.963 --> 1:44:53.829
was caught up in Veronica's web.

1:44:55.228 --> 1:44:55.862
Mrs. Smart.

1:44:55.895 --> 1:44:56.762
I would love that.

1:44:56.762 --> 1:44:59.228
I, I want to learn everything from you.

1:44:59.228 --> 1:45:01.495
And I will teach you everything

1:45:01.495 --> 1:45:02.561
that you want to know.

1:45:04.693 --> 1:45:07.994
I've never had any real friends before.

1:45:08.527 --> 1:45:10.027
Oh, well, except Betty, and she's well,

1:45:10.627 --> 1:45:11.559
she's just a kid.

1:45:12.793 --> 1:45:14.093
I've never really had anybody

1:45:14.093 --> 1:45:15.493
that truly understands me.

1:45:16.293 --> 1:45:17.226
Everybody just

1:45:18.459 --> 1:45:19.392
passed me by.

1:45:21.559 --> 1:45:22.657
I hope you know how much

1:45:22.657 --> 1:45:24.058
I value our relationship.

1:45:24.325 --> 1:45:26.291
Oh, as do I, Vivian.

1:45:27.157 --> 1:45:28.124
So why don't we say

1:45:28.491 --> 1:45:29.891
eight thirty tomorrow night?

1:45:30.091 --> 1:45:31.257
Perhaps you could tell your mother

1:45:31.257 --> 1:45:32.523
you're staying at a friend's place.

1:45:32.590 --> 1:45:33.957
My mother doesn't control me.

1:45:34.157 --> 1:45:35.357
I want to be like you.

1:45:35.357 --> 1:45:36.823
Strong. Confident.

1:45:37.057 --> 1:45:37.590
I'm afraid.

1:45:37.590 --> 1:45:39.990
I don't feel very strong lately.

1:45:40.123 --> 1:45:40.423
Vivian.

1:45:40.723 --> 1:45:41.489
What do you mean?

1:45:43.522 --> 1:45:45.822
My life is is complicated.

1:45:46.522 --> 1:45:47.222
Mr. Smart?

1:45:49.621 --> 1:45:51.487
You know, I used to be like you, Vivian.

1:45:51.487 --> 1:45:54.621
I dreamed of a life in the spotlight.

1:45:54.987 --> 1:45:56.554
People calling my name

1:45:56.887 --> 1:45:58.187
surrounded by glamour

1:45:58.187 --> 1:46:00.153
and most of all, friends.

1:46:00.287 --> 1:46:02.686
But the day I married Cliff,

1:46:02.686 --> 1:46:04.286
I think I let a part of that die.

1:46:04.486 --> 1:46:06.519
No, no, it's still in there.

1:46:07.386 --> 1:46:08.152
Perhaps. But

1:46:09.486 --> 1:46:10.352
I think every time

1:46:10.352 --> 1:46:11.785
Cliff strikes my face,

1:46:13.052 --> 1:46:14.318
he takes a little more of me.

1:46:16.518 --> 1:46:17.085
Veronica.

1:46:17.851 --> 1:46:18.918
You don't need a man.

1:46:19.418 --> 1:46:20.617
I mean, why do any of us

1:46:20.617 --> 1:46:21.584
need men, really?

1:46:21.916 --> 1:46:23.517
They always ruin everything.

1:46:26.250 --> 1:46:27.583
My father's idea of raising

1:46:27.583 --> 1:46:28.782
a child is shouting at it

1:46:28.883 --> 1:46:32.183
when called on by my mother.

1:46:32.648 --> 1:46:33.749
Maybe...

1:46:34.216 --> 1:46:35.749
Maybe what sweetheart?

1:46:36.349 --> 1:46:38.215
Maybe we can move to Hollywood together.

1:46:38.582 --> 1:46:39.715
Two girls ready to

1:46:39.715 --> 1:46:40.981
take on the big screen.

1:46:40.981 --> 1:46:42.880
Oh, Hollywood won't know what hit it.

1:46:43.114 --> 1:46:44.681
You could leave Cliff.

1:46:44.681 --> 1:46:46.681
We could just drive there together.

1:46:46.681 --> 1:46:48.414
Oh, Veronica, imagine.

1:46:49.714 --> 1:46:51.513
Well, that sounds wonderful, Vivian.

1:46:51.947 --> 1:46:54.213
A dream, but wonderful.

1:46:55.213 --> 1:46:56.546
It doesn't have to be.

1:46:57.246 --> 1:46:58.912
Cliff is so awful to you.

1:46:58.912 --> 1:47:00.344
Why can't he just drop dead?

1:47:00.379 --> 1:47:02.145
Oh, Vivian, you shouldn't

1:47:02.145 --> 1:47:03.245
say such a thing.

1:47:03.577 --> 1:47:05.311
Well, you'd feel positively awful

1:47:05.311 --> 1:47:06.911
if something were to happen to him now.

1:47:07.445 --> 1:47:08.710
I doubt it.

1:47:10.311 --> 1:47:10.977
Look, Vivian,

1:47:10.977 --> 1:47:13.344
I need to head into town, so.

1:47:13.377 --> 1:47:14.677
Oh, oh.

1:47:14.943 --> 1:47:16.410
Sorry, I'll go.

1:47:17.043 --> 1:47:18.943
Oh, shall we say.

1:47:19.276 --> 1:47:20.409
Eight thirty tomorrow.

1:47:20.409 --> 1:47:21.709
Outside the front of the school?

1:47:22.143 --> 1:47:23.776
Sure Veronica, I can um,

1:47:25.109 --> 1:47:26.142
I can hardly wait.

1:47:36.174 --> 1:47:37.574
Why don't you, uh

1:47:38.307 --> 1:47:40.007
come sit on my lap,

1:47:40.507 --> 1:47:42.173
let daddy take care of you.

1:47:43.273 --> 1:47:44.940
OK, baby,

1:47:45.773 --> 1:47:47.073
you like that daddy?

1:47:47.573 --> 1:47:48.639
I do indeed.

1:47:49.772 --> 1:47:50.306
So

1:47:51.739 --> 1:47:52.539
how are you

1:47:53.305 --> 1:47:54.838
going to make your old man happy?

1:47:55.737 --> 1:47:57.505
Whatever you want me to do,

1:47:57.971 --> 1:47:59.671
you're paying.

1:48:00.371 --> 1:48:01.504
Don't talk like that.

1:48:03.570 --> 1:48:06.170
Don't talk like a whore.

1:48:06.503 --> 1:48:08.436
OK baby.

1:48:11.969 --> 1:48:13.236
Jimmy.

1:48:13.736 --> 1:48:14.602
I thought I told you

1:48:14.602 --> 1:48:16.135
stay away tonight, I had company.

1:48:16.869 --> 1:48:18.768
Hi dollface, I'm the company.

1:48:18.768 --> 1:48:19.402
I'm sorry.

1:48:19.402 --> 1:48:19.968
I forgot.

1:48:20.102 --> 1:48:21.768
Are you trying to be lippy with me?

1:48:22.068 --> 1:48:23.268
Look dad, I've had a tough day.

1:48:23.268 --> 1:48:23.968
I want to go to bed.

1:48:24.334 --> 1:48:25.867
Tough day?

1:48:25.867 --> 1:48:28.267
My kid, sixteen, at high school.

1:48:28.267 --> 1:48:29.700
Thinks he's had a tough day.

1:48:30.267 --> 1:48:32.567
You don't even know what a tough day is.

1:48:33.000 --> 1:48:34.400
You try breaking your back

1:48:34.400 --> 1:48:35.400
every day at work.

1:48:35.566 --> 1:48:38.066
Then you can tell me about a tough day.

1:48:38.732 --> 1:48:40.199
Look, I should go Harvey.

1:48:40.199 --> 1:48:41.764
Sit down!

1:48:43.432 --> 1:48:45.132
You're not going anywhere tonight.

1:48:45.465 --> 1:48:48.130
I'd get out of here if I were you.

1:48:48.130 --> 1:48:49.464
He likes to use his fists

1:48:49.464 --> 1:48:50.597
to beat the women around him.

1:48:51.231 --> 1:48:52.364
Harvey, I'm out of here.

1:48:56.563 --> 1:48:57.930
Do it, go on.

1:48:58.463 --> 1:48:59.830
Let me tell you something, Jimmy Flynn.

1:49:00.896 --> 1:49:02.496
I have protected you from this for years.

1:49:02.596 --> 1:49:03.929
I will not let you talk

1:49:03.929 --> 1:49:04.762
that way about me.

1:49:07.129 --> 1:49:09.495
Your mom was a drunk.

1:49:09.928 --> 1:49:11.695
She would come home every night

1:49:11.695 --> 1:49:13.728
starting a fight throwing things,

1:49:13.728 --> 1:49:14.228
hitting me.

1:49:14.228 --> 1:49:15.094
That's a lie.

1:49:15.094 --> 1:49:16.727
She left you outside of church

1:49:16.727 --> 1:49:18.394
when you were just seven months old.

1:49:18.794 --> 1:49:19.994
She wanted to go to some bar,

1:49:19.994 --> 1:49:21.893
but you were in the way.

1:49:21.893 --> 1:49:22.960
So I came to get you again.

1:49:22.993 --> 1:49:24.226
Why are you lying?

1:49:24.260 --> 1:49:25.759
She screwed every man

1:49:25.759 --> 1:49:27.826
without a single thought of you and me.

1:49:28.626 --> 1:49:30.791
So, yeah, you may see me

1:49:30.791 --> 1:49:31.992
as the bad guy, and yeah,

1:49:33.525 --> 1:49:34.925
I ain't perfect,

1:49:35.458 --> 1:49:36.725
you know what,

1:49:37.657 --> 1:49:38.891
I'm still here.

1:49:39.758 --> 1:49:41.124
I'm still here.

1:49:41.124 --> 1:49:42.191
No, no, no.

1:49:42.424 --> 1:49:43.824
You pushed her away.

1:49:44.790 --> 1:49:47.057
Women lie Jimmy, always

1:49:47.057 --> 1:49:49.323
remember that, women lie.

1:49:51.423 --> 1:49:55.456
No dad, that's you.

1:49:56.121 --> 1:49:59.555
Life is easier without them.

1:50:00.821 --> 1:50:03.154
I got mine back when she left.

1:50:04.788 --> 1:50:06.021
And look at you, dad.

1:50:08.520 --> 1:50:09.420
You're an embarrassment.

1:50:11.187 --> 1:50:12.153
Spending all the money

1:50:12.153 --> 1:50:13.853
that you make on booze and whores.

1:50:13.886 --> 1:50:15.452
I never, ever

1:50:16.686 --> 1:50:17.886
want to turn out like you.

1:50:18.252 --> 1:50:19.452
Jimmy.

1:50:19.452 --> 1:50:20.318
I know love.

1:50:21.684 --> 1:50:22.452
I've found love,

1:50:22.452 --> 1:50:23.952
I'd kill for love and I tell you

1:50:23.952 --> 1:50:25.318
I've never felt more alive.

1:50:25.318 --> 1:50:27.651
So if you want to fade away,

1:50:28.918 --> 1:50:30.451
then that's fine.

1:50:31.550 --> 1:50:33.317
But I ain't going down with you.

1:50:33.317 --> 1:50:34.617
Do you hear me, old man?

1:50:34.817 --> 1:50:35.983
I ain't going down with you.

1:50:39.050 --> 1:50:42.049
(Train Sounds)

1:50:58.447 --> 1:50:59.214
Ha!

1:51:01.413 --> 1:51:02.680
Well, you look like

1:51:02.680 --> 1:51:03.112
you've got the weight

1:51:03.112 --> 1:51:04.213
of the world on shoulders.

1:51:04.380 --> 1:51:05.879
Now that I could handle.

1:51:05.879 --> 1:51:06.513
What's going on?

1:51:07.246 --> 1:51:08.046
Why aren't you with Jimmy?

1:51:08.213 --> 1:51:09.612
We're not joined at the hip you know.

1:51:09.612 --> 1:51:11.512
No, but you seem to share a brain.

1:51:11.512 --> 1:51:12.012
Haha,

1:51:12.012 --> 1:51:14.312
you should have been a circus clown.

1:51:14.512 --> 1:51:15.012
Riff!

1:51:15.012 --> 1:51:16.611
What happened to your face?

1:51:16.611 --> 1:51:19.244
I walked into a fist, it's New York City,

1:51:19.244 --> 1:51:20.111
what are you gonna do.

1:51:20.844 --> 1:51:21.511
Well, are you OK?

1:51:21.811 --> 1:51:23.011
Honestly, I'm fine.

1:51:27.077 --> 1:51:29.010
Vivian, can I ask you something?

1:51:29.010 --> 1:51:29.543
Sure,

1:51:30.143 --> 1:51:31.743
as long as it's not asking me on a date.

1:51:31.843 --> 1:51:33.043
Not a date, fear not.

1:51:35.276 --> 1:51:36.342
Do you trust Veronica?

1:51:36.375 --> 1:51:37.409
What do you mean trust her?

1:51:37.442 --> 1:51:38.407
You know, the thing

1:51:38.407 --> 1:51:39.808
she says the things about Cliff.

1:51:39.808 --> 1:51:41.075
He's a monster Riff.

1:51:41.075 --> 1:51:42.475
Veronica is one of the most honest

1:51:42.475 --> 1:51:44.308
and trustworthy people I've ever met.

1:51:44.508 --> 1:51:45.674
DIal it down, you sound like you

1:51:45.674 --> 1:51:46.341
run her fan club.

1:51:46.574 --> 1:51:48.074
Well, Veronica cares about us.

1:51:48.107 --> 1:51:49.940
I mean, she's more of a mother to me...

1:51:49.940 --> 1:51:50.540
Yeah, but...

1:51:50.540 --> 1:51:52.340
Yeah, but nothing Riff Randall.

1:51:52.340 --> 1:51:55.373
I mean, Veronica has taught me so much.

1:51:55.540 --> 1:51:57.039
I mean, she stopped and gave me,

1:51:57.073 --> 1:51:58.639
gave us the time of day.

1:51:59.439 --> 1:52:00.272
I mean, what other adult

1:52:00.339 --> 1:52:01.605
wants to listen to us, huh?

1:52:02.039 --> 1:52:04.105
Like really listen.

1:52:04.772 --> 1:52:06.505
Oh Vivian, I'm wrestling

1:52:06.505 --> 1:52:07.671
with something real bad.

1:52:08.105 --> 1:52:10.871
What are you talking about, Riff?

1:52:10.871 --> 1:52:11.804
Can I trust you

1:52:12.804 --> 1:52:14.337
that no matter what I say,

1:52:14.337 --> 1:52:15.469
it stays between us.

1:52:15.704 --> 1:52:17.337
This is serious, Vivian,

1:52:17.337 --> 1:52:19.170
and it isn't some silly, childish thing.

1:52:19.270 --> 1:52:20.603
I don't know if you've noticed but

1:52:20.603 --> 1:52:22.436
I've done a lot of growing up recently.

1:52:22.702 --> 1:52:24.002
So I swear to you,

1:52:24.335 --> 1:52:25.436
I'll take it to the grave.

1:52:27.235 --> 1:52:29.335
Veronica has asked Jimmy to kill Cliff.

1:52:32.268 --> 1:52:33.268
What?

1:52:33.268 --> 1:52:35.201
Jimmy's asked me to be involved as well.

1:52:35.201 --> 1:52:36.434
And it's a thousand bucks,

1:52:36.434 --> 1:52:37.734
which is more money than I ever

1:52:37.734 --> 1:52:38.234
thought I'd see.

1:52:38.234 --> 1:52:39.100
But I can't, can I?

1:52:40.000 --> 1:52:40.967
Woah Riff.

1:52:40.967 --> 1:52:41.967
Slow down.

1:52:42.100 --> 1:52:43.233
I know he beats her.

1:52:43.233 --> 1:52:44.532
At least that's what she says, but

1:52:44.933 --> 1:52:46.833
murder is just so final, you know,

1:52:46.866 --> 1:52:48.166
I mean, how could I live with that?

1:52:49.532 --> 1:52:51.132
When is this supposed to happen?

1:52:51.599 --> 1:52:53.732
Tomorrow night, he's gone girl crazy.

1:52:53.865 --> 1:52:54.832
It's like he thinks that

1:52:54.832 --> 1:52:56.598
if he kills Cliff, Veronica

1:52:56.598 --> 1:52:57.898
will fall madly in love with him.

1:52:57.898 --> 1:53:00.398
The whole thing is just hairbrained.

1:53:00.764 --> 1:53:02.931
Jeez, killing her husband

1:53:02.931 --> 1:53:05.130
to prove his love for her.

1:53:05.130 --> 1:53:06.397
Ain't that something.

1:53:06.397 --> 1:53:08.696
Should I call the police?

1:53:08.696 --> 1:53:10.563
Should I try to stop him? No, no, no.

1:53:10.596 --> 1:53:11.929
He'll go to prison Riff.

1:53:11.929 --> 1:53:13.596
You need to be there and stop him

1:53:13.596 --> 1:53:15.196
from making a stupid mistake.

1:53:15.396 --> 1:53:16.495
He won't listen to me.

1:53:16.529 --> 1:53:17.795
I've already tried.

1:53:17.929 --> 1:53:18.962
Well, if he doesn't,

1:53:18.995 --> 1:53:20.327
then go to the police.

1:53:20.562 --> 1:53:21.761
Just, just stop it.

1:53:22.195 --> 1:53:24.361
This could ruin his life and Veronicas is

1:53:24.394 --> 1:53:25.327
if they get caught.

1:53:25.861 --> 1:53:28.261
We can't allow that to happen Riff.

1:53:28.261 --> 1:53:30.027
Vivian, you better

1:53:30.027 --> 1:53:31.660
not be down by the tracks.

1:53:32.327 --> 1:53:35.925
She is driving me crazy.

1:53:37.093 --> 1:53:38.992
God, killing Cliff.

1:53:38.992 --> 1:53:41.159
Riff, you need to stop it.

1:53:41.192 --> 1:53:44.125
We can't allow Veronica to get hurt.

1:53:44.325 --> 1:53:45.825
She could get sent away

1:53:45.825 --> 1:53:46.691
if she gets caught,

1:53:46.691 --> 1:53:48.258
and that's not the way for her

1:53:48.258 --> 1:53:49.324
to get away from Cliff.

1:53:49.458 --> 1:53:51.624
Veronica, you worried about Veronica?

1:53:52.457 --> 1:53:53.057
I've got to go.

1:53:53.057 --> 1:53:53.624
I'm sorry.

1:53:53.690 --> 1:53:55.590
Vivian, but that's not the whole story.

1:53:55.889 --> 1:53:58.490
I still have more need to say, Vivian!

1:54:01.223 --> 1:54:04.222
(Train Sounds)

1:54:10.522 --> 1:54:12.355
It's 7:30 a.m. on the big day, Cliff.

1:54:12.355 --> 1:54:12.987
Well, Cliff

1:54:14.388 --> 1:54:15.388
wakes up to a life

1:54:15.388 --> 1:54:16.454
he could only dream of.

1:54:17.321 --> 1:54:18.554
Cliff stands and stares

1:54:18.554 --> 1:54:20.020
at Veronica for a few moments

1:54:20.587 --> 1:54:21.787
as she prepares breakfast.

1:54:23.520 --> 1:54:24.886
I want to remember this moment.

1:54:25.053 --> 1:54:26.786
Oh, Cliff, you startled me.

1:54:27.919 --> 1:54:29.386
I feel like I'm looking at a new you.

1:54:30.585 --> 1:54:31.318
What's the occasion?

1:54:31.885 --> 1:54:33.318
It's just breakfast.

1:54:34.452 --> 1:54:35.085
I'm already late.

1:54:36.585 --> 1:54:37.485
I've got a big day,

1:54:39.318 --> 1:54:40.550
but I can take it to go.

1:54:41.651 --> 1:54:42.984
You're always on the move.

1:54:47.916 --> 1:54:48.416
Oh, and

1:54:50.383 --> 1:54:50.883
Veronica.

1:54:53.982 --> 1:54:55.482
I always loved you.

1:54:56.582 --> 1:54:58.148
Whatever happened,

1:54:59.715 --> 1:55:00.615
I wanted you to know that.

1:55:01.781 --> 1:55:02.715
UInexpectedly, tears

1:55:02.715 --> 1:55:04.414
form in Veronica's eyes.

1:55:05.148 --> 1:55:06.781
These ain't no acting tears.

1:55:07.614 --> 1:55:10.147
Veronica appears moved,

1:55:10.847 --> 1:55:12.280
moved by Cliffs words.

1:55:13.180 --> 1:55:15.612
The man she's about to have killed.

1:55:17.179 --> 1:55:17.978
Veronica.

1:55:18.079 --> 1:55:20.679
Jimmy, Jimmy you startled me.

1:55:24.577 --> 1:55:25.912
You having second thoughts?

1:55:26.112 --> 1:55:27.011
What?

1:55:27.545 --> 1:55:30.878
No, no Jimmy, it's

1:55:30.878 --> 1:55:32.477
me and you from now on.

1:55:32.477 --> 1:55:33.977
Our future begins tonight.

1:55:35.277 --> 1:55:36.577
When can we leave for Hollywood?

1:55:37.010 --> 1:55:38.743
A week, maybe two.

1:55:39.543 --> 1:55:40.143
I just don't want it

1:55:40.143 --> 1:55:41.210
to look as though I'm

1:55:41.210 --> 1:55:41.843
fleeing.

1:55:43.675 --> 1:55:46.242
God, I love you Veronica Smart.

1:55:59.040 --> 1:56:01.474
So you get here at eight o'clock.

1:56:02.139 --> 1:56:03.040
Cliff would have just

1:56:03.040 --> 1:56:03.807
come home from work,

1:56:03.807 --> 1:56:04.940
you'll catch him off guard.

1:56:05.373 --> 1:56:07.106
I have an alibi in place.

1:56:08.239 --> 1:56:12.505
There is nothing that can stand in our way

1:56:19.404 --> 1:56:20.338
Jimmy.

1:56:20.338 --> 1:56:23.271
Hey, Sal Salazar's fighting tonight.

1:56:23.871 --> 1:56:26.037
Why don't you and I have a night in.

1:56:26.637 --> 1:56:29.370
Watch the fight, have a couple of beers.

1:56:30.236 --> 1:56:30.936
I can't dad,

1:56:30.936 --> 1:56:31.969
I've got something I need to do.

1:56:33.103 --> 1:56:34.436
I'm trying here Jimmy.

1:56:36.335 --> 1:56:39.102
You have no idea how it feels to be

1:56:39.102 --> 1:56:41.302
invisible, do you, mother?

1:56:44.201 --> 1:56:44.901
You know, I sit

1:56:46.001 --> 1:56:47.034
and watch the movies

1:56:47.034 --> 1:56:50.500
and see these beautiful women,

1:56:51.700 --> 1:56:52.700
so full of life,

1:56:52.700 --> 1:56:54.700
their eyes sparkle like diamonds,

1:56:57.032 --> 1:56:59.366
and they seem happy.

1:57:01.665 --> 1:57:03.764
Really happy,

1:57:06.032 --> 1:57:07.465
and then

1:57:07.865 --> 1:57:09.364
I look in the mirror and I see,

1:57:13.064 --> 1:57:13.431
me.

1:57:15.864 --> 1:57:16.496
Dad.

1:57:18.563 --> 1:57:19.963
That woman you said you loved,

1:57:24.196 --> 1:57:24.662
Patricia?

1:57:27.662 --> 1:57:28.895
What about her?

1:57:28.895 --> 1:57:30.862
Why didn't you fight for her?

1:57:32.695 --> 1:57:33.895
How do you know I didn't?

1:57:34.161 --> 1:57:36.061
Well, did you?

1:57:37.161 --> 1:57:38.627
How could I Jimmy.

1:57:39.027 --> 1:57:40.427
She made a choice

1:57:41.027 --> 1:57:41.860
as soon as she let

1:57:41.860 --> 1:57:43.360
that other guy into her bed,

1:57:45.360 --> 1:57:46.460
it was all over.

1:57:47.793 --> 1:57:48.559
Those women on the screen

1:57:48.559 --> 1:57:50.259
aren't like that in real life.

1:57:50.259 --> 1:57:52.425
They have the best makeup

1:57:52.425 --> 1:57:53.592
people and the best gowns.

1:57:53.692 --> 1:57:54.825
And I want that.

1:57:55.992 --> 1:57:57.025
I hate my life.

1:57:57.091 --> 1:57:58.625
I just want to be beautiful,

1:57:58.625 --> 1:58:00.258
why is that so wrong?

1:58:00.258 --> 1:58:01.523
Oh, Vivian you are beautiful.

1:58:01.523 --> 1:58:02.991
Stop it, mother.

1:58:05.690 --> 1:58:08.323
Veronica is making me beautiful.

1:58:09.990 --> 1:58:10.690
Look at me.

1:58:12.623 --> 1:58:13.156
Maybe.

1:58:16.089 --> 1:58:17.121
Maybe she made a mistake,

1:58:18.955 --> 1:58:20.755
got married for the wrong reasons,

1:58:20.755 --> 1:58:21.888
maybe she was waiting for you

1:58:21.888 --> 1:58:22.788
to come and save her.

1:58:24.987 --> 1:58:25.388
Jimmy?

1:58:26.554 --> 1:58:27.621
What is this all about?

1:58:28.087 --> 1:58:29.054
You listen to me.

1:58:31.387 --> 1:58:33.187
You are 15 years old.

1:58:34.920 --> 1:58:35.719
You haven't even fully

1:58:35.719 --> 1:58:37.153
blossomed as a woman yet.

1:58:38.818 --> 1:58:39.686
But I see you,

1:58:41.286 --> 1:58:42.419
I see you are beautiful

1:58:43.318 --> 1:58:44.585
and you don't need to hide behind

1:58:44.585 --> 1:58:45.785
this paint to show that.

1:58:47.318 --> 1:58:49.285
Nothing that I got to go, Jimmy.

1:58:51.818 --> 1:58:52.884
Should I be worried about you?

1:58:54.384 --> 1:58:54.850
What do you mean?

1:58:55.916 --> 1:58:56.317
Well,

1:58:57.483 --> 1:59:01.416
this woman, are you serious about her?

1:59:01.416 --> 1:59:02.583
I've never been more serious

1:59:02.583 --> 1:59:03.683
about anything in my life.

1:59:04.716 --> 1:59:05.982
You have to find your own way,

1:59:05.982 --> 1:59:07.582
you can't just become somebody else.

1:59:07.615 --> 1:59:08.382
That's not true.

1:59:09.682 --> 1:59:11.514
Veronica said that many movie

1:59:11.514 --> 1:59:12.915
stars come from lives like mine.

1:59:12.915 --> 1:59:14.614
They get to change their name and

1:59:14.614 --> 1:59:15.814
they're weight and their hair.

1:59:15.814 --> 1:59:17.847
You know how many girls feel like you?

1:59:19.147 --> 1:59:20.514
All wanting the same thing.

1:59:21.180 --> 1:59:22.213
So should I be worried?

1:59:23.280 --> 1:59:23.713
Worried.

1:59:26.213 --> 1:59:27.279
About love?

1:59:29.213 --> 1:59:32.245
No dad you don't need to be worried.

1:59:34.478 --> 1:59:35.612
I know that she's the one.

1:59:36.645 --> 1:59:37.210
Veronica...

1:59:37.210 --> 1:59:38.911
Ahh, Veronica!

1:59:39.544 --> 1:59:41.077
I don't want to be your enemy

1:59:41.378 --> 1:59:42.877
and I want you to succeed.

1:59:44.077 --> 1:59:45.144
But we have few options

1:59:45.144 --> 1:59:46.309
in life as women, Vivian,

1:59:46.910 --> 1:59:47.943
so we have to work harder,

1:59:47.943 --> 1:59:48.877
and that's all I want

1:59:48.877 --> 1:59:50.309
you to do is work harder.

1:59:51.776 --> 1:59:53.943
You know, that is the first time

1:59:53.943 --> 1:59:56.009
you have told me her name.

1:59:56.009 --> 1:59:56.342
Yeah.

1:59:58.075 --> 1:59:59.808
Veronica, Veronica.

2:00:01.808 --> 2:00:03.241
I don't think I know her.

2:00:03.241 --> 2:00:06.441
Well, apart from your teacher.

2:00:13.007 --> 2:00:15.906
Well, I am working harder mother,

2:00:17.673 --> 2:00:18.406
but this time

2:00:19.506 --> 2:00:20.172
it's for me.

2:00:21.372 --> 2:00:21.972
Not you.

2:00:22.672 --> 2:00:24.172
Oh, Vivian.

2:00:24.172 --> 2:00:24.905
Mother I have to go.

2:00:25.605 --> 2:00:27.471
Please tell me you're not involved

2:00:27.471 --> 2:00:28.571
with your teacher.

2:00:28.871 --> 2:00:29.871
I have to go and find Riff,

2:00:29.871 --> 2:00:30.971
and if I can't find him

2:00:30.971 --> 2:00:31.804
I have to find Veronica and stop...

2:00:31.804 --> 2:00:32.304
Stop what?

2:00:32.337 --> 2:00:33.904
What are you talking about?

2:00:33.971 --> 2:00:36.337
I got to go, I won't be late.

2:00:36.504 --> 2:00:36.770
Jimmy please.

2:00:36.770 --> 2:00:37.803
Jimmy stop.

2:00:37.803 --> 2:00:39.037
Jimmy!

2:00:50.335 --> 2:00:52.168
Riff, Riff?

2:00:52.168 --> 2:00:53.435
Is that you?

2:00:56.301 --> 2:00:57.501
So have you got the gun?

2:00:57.534 --> 2:00:59.034
I'm sorry Jimmy I ain't got it.

2:00:59.334 --> 2:01:00.234
The guy never gave it me back.

2:01:00.234 --> 2:01:01.134
And he's vanished.

2:01:01.267 --> 2:01:02.767
Damn it Riff. I need that.

2:01:02.867 --> 2:01:04.633
You don't have to go through with this.

2:01:05.600 --> 2:01:06.400
You really don't have it?

2:01:06.766 --> 2:01:07.233
Sorry.

2:01:07.533 --> 2:01:09.633
Oh, well, that's perfect Riff.

2:01:11.732 --> 2:01:13.232
To hell with it, I still got my bat.

2:01:13.465 --> 2:01:14.732
Don't do this.

2:01:14.732 --> 2:01:15.932
You'll ruin your life.

2:01:16.198 --> 2:01:17.065
If I don't do something,

2:01:17.065 --> 2:01:18.431
and he hurts my baby

2:01:19.131 --> 2:01:20.631
how am I supposed to live with that?

2:01:20.898 --> 2:01:21.998
You think your some kind of mobster

2:01:21.998 --> 2:01:23.131
now cause you are gonna kill a guy?

2:01:23.131 --> 2:01:24.164
Oh Riff, go home

2:01:24.164 --> 2:01:24.897
if you don't want to help,

2:01:24.897 --> 2:01:25.897
you ain't got to be here.

2:01:26.197 --> 2:01:27.030
Jimmy.

2:01:27.397 --> 2:01:28.197
Jimmy, look at me.

2:01:28.697 --> 2:01:29.730
all the things you could

2:01:29.730 --> 2:01:30.363
do with your life.

2:01:30.363 --> 2:01:32.763
I don't need anything else

2:01:32.763 --> 2:01:34.263
just her and my kid.

2:01:34.263 --> 2:01:34.696
You're a kid yourself.

2:01:34.696 --> 2:01:36.062
Jimmy, how are you going to raise a kid?

2:01:36.329 --> 2:01:37.096
Riff, go home,

2:01:38.295 --> 2:01:38.995
please.

2:01:39.329 --> 2:01:40.962
Once you're marked by the devil Jimmy,

2:01:40.962 --> 2:01:42.028
you can't come back from that.

2:01:42.295 --> 2:01:43.595
Believe me, I know.

2:01:43.595 --> 2:01:44.628
Some things are worth it.

2:01:45.061 --> 2:01:46.328
I'll call the police, Jimmy.

2:01:46.328 --> 2:01:47.727
No, you won't Riff, that ain't you.

2:01:47.761 --> 2:01:49.327
Jimmy, please just listen to me.

2:01:49.327 --> 2:01:50.960
I really needed that gun.

2:01:50.960 --> 2:01:51.860
Call it off.

2:01:51.860 --> 2:01:52.327
No way.

2:01:56.760 --> 2:01:57.426
It just means that

2:01:57.426 --> 2:01:58.959
I have to do this myself.

2:02:00.459 --> 2:02:01.592
Like a man.

2:02:01.592 --> 2:02:02.359
Jimmy please.

2:02:02.359 --> 2:02:03.559
It's going to be fine Riff.

2:02:04.858 --> 2:02:05.425
Trust me.

2:02:06.758 --> 2:02:08.491
In a few hours,

2:02:09.858 --> 2:02:10.758
all this is over.

2:02:14.191 --> 2:02:15.724
Dammit Jimmy.

2:02:17.124 --> 2:02:18.457
I'm sorry.

2:02:20.723 --> 2:02:21.590
A plan.

2:02:21.590 --> 2:02:24.023
A man ain't a man without a plan.

2:02:24.922 --> 2:02:26.089
It's February 13th,

2:02:26.689 --> 2:02:28.922
just after 7.30 that same evening,

2:02:29.922 --> 2:02:32.188
silence washes over the neighborhood.

2:02:32.188 --> 2:02:35.188
A figure seen at the back of the house

2:02:35.321 --> 2:02:36.554
heads towards the back door.

2:02:37.487 --> 2:02:38.621
The figure stands in front

2:02:38.621 --> 2:02:39.454
of it for a moment

2:02:40.054 --> 2:02:41.454
and then knocks on the door.

2:02:42.553 --> 2:02:44.353
As the door opens, however.

2:02:45.153 --> 2:02:48.086
Well, it's not Cliff, It's Veronica,

2:02:49.053 --> 2:02:50.319
and it's not Jimmy stood

2:02:50.319 --> 2:02:53.752
there, it's Riff.

2:02:54.952 --> 2:02:55.718
Riff, what are you doing here?

2:02:56.352 --> 2:02:57.085
You're early.

2:02:57.118 --> 2:02:58.285
I have to leave first,

2:02:58.285 --> 2:03:00.784
and then you come back when Cliff's home.

2:03:00.784 --> 2:03:01.284
Jesus, I thought

2:03:01.318 --> 2:03:02.851
Jimmy went through the plan with you.

2:03:03.717 --> 2:03:04.117
Mrs Smart.

2:03:04.517 --> 2:03:06.217
Where is Jimmy is he not with you.

2:03:07.717 --> 2:03:08.717
Is that the gun?

2:03:09.583 --> 2:03:10.750
I thought you gave that to Jimmy.

2:03:11.583 --> 2:03:12.649
In fact, I thought you said

2:03:12.649 --> 2:03:13.883
you didn't want any part of this.

2:03:13.883 --> 2:03:15.082
Mrs Smart.

2:03:15.082 --> 2:03:16.249
Now run along Riff,

2:03:16.249 --> 2:03:17.349
I need to get out of here,

2:03:17.349 --> 2:03:18.715
go and meet Vivian.

2:03:20.548 --> 2:03:21.282
Riff?

2:03:22.715 --> 2:03:24.381
Riff, what are you doing?

2:03:24.781 --> 2:03:25.214
Aaahh!

2:03:25.914 --> 2:03:26.948
Yes, Riff.

2:03:27.181 --> 2:03:28.614
What are you doing?

2:03:29.014 --> 2:03:30.380
Let's go back to the moment

2:03:30.414 --> 2:03:32.713
Riff and Cliff came face to face.

2:03:32.713 --> 2:03:34.947
It was like a showdown in the Wild West,

2:03:34.947 --> 2:03:36.980
but who would flinch first?

2:03:38.346 --> 2:03:40.612
We still have unfinished business kid.

2:03:41.079 --> 2:03:41.912
Mr. Smart.

2:03:52.911 --> 2:03:54.444
Did you really think

2:03:54.444 --> 2:03:55.044
I was going to let

2:03:55.044 --> 2:03:56.177
you get away with that kid?

2:03:56.177 --> 2:03:57.777
Please Mr Smart, I'm sorry.

2:03:57.777 --> 2:03:58.810
You think you can jump

2:03:58.810 --> 2:03:59.677
me, you little punk?

2:03:59.843 --> 2:04:00.843
It was a mistake, please.

2:04:00.876 --> 2:04:04.343
I didn't know you were Veronicas husband.

2:04:04.343 --> 2:04:05.409
You made a joke out of me

2:04:05.409 --> 2:04:06.242
for the last time.

2:04:06.709 --> 2:04:08.909
You're nothing, street trash.

2:04:09.209 --> 2:04:10.508
I should do the world a favour

2:04:10.508 --> 2:04:11.742
and put you out of your misery.

2:04:11.875 --> 2:04:13.175
Please don't do this.

2:04:13.175 --> 2:04:15.274
I'm a good kid, I didn't mean to hurt you.

2:04:15.574 --> 2:04:16.841
You ain't a good kid Riff.

2:04:16.841 --> 2:04:18.174
Please, please, please.

2:04:18.174 --> 2:04:19.741
Oh God, oh God, oh God!

2:04:19.741 --> 2:04:20.974
So tell me Riff,

2:04:20.974 --> 2:04:22.840
are you sleeping with my wife?

2:04:23.740 --> 2:04:24.573
No, no.

2:04:24.607 --> 2:04:25.640
Why would you think that?

2:04:26.740 --> 2:04:28.206
I think you are.

2:04:28.206 --> 2:04:30.339
Now, Is it just you

2:04:30.672 --> 2:04:31.772
or is it Jimmy as well?

2:04:31.806 --> 2:04:33.005
You got it all wrong.

2:04:34.805 --> 2:04:36.238
Ahhh, it's Jimmy.

2:04:37.505 --> 2:04:38.471
Jimmy's stepping out with your wife,

2:04:38.471 --> 2:04:39.638
not me, I swear.

2:04:39.971 --> 2:04:41.638
Give me a Bible and i'll swear on it.

2:04:43.804 --> 2:04:44.904
Jimmy, that son of a bitch!

2:04:45.304 --> 2:04:47.704
Please just let me go.

2:04:47.704 --> 2:04:48.670
I ain't going to cause you

2:04:48.670 --> 2:04:49.437
any more problems.

2:04:49.437 --> 2:04:51.236
You give me one damn reason I should.

2:04:51.403 --> 2:04:53.536
Because I'm just 16.

2:04:53.536 --> 2:04:55.402
I ain't moved.

2:04:57.536 --> 2:04:59.735
Your wife has hired Jimmy to murder you.

2:05:01.368 --> 2:05:02.868
You're lying.

2:05:02.868 --> 2:05:04.235
No, I ain't, he is supposed

2:05:04.235 --> 2:05:05.135
to do it this week?

2:05:05.501 --> 2:05:07.401
She wants your money and Jimmy,

2:05:07.401 --> 2:05:07.901
I swear to you,

2:05:08.101 --> 2:05:09.134
I ain't stupid enough to be lying

2:05:09.134 --> 2:05:10.300
to you right now.

2:05:10.300 --> 2:05:11.900
No, no, she's having my baby.

2:05:12.400 --> 2:05:14.700
She said the same thing to Jimmy.

2:05:21.332 --> 2:05:24.865
Veronica, you've made a joke out of me

2:05:24.865 --> 2:05:26.265
for the last time.

2:05:26.265 --> 2:05:29.431
Oh God, what have I done?

2:05:29.431 --> 2:05:31.964
You just saved your own life kid.

2:05:31.964 --> 2:05:32.498
Now

2:05:33.497 --> 2:05:34.564
you're working for me.

2:05:35.264 --> 2:05:36.030
Do you understand?

2:05:37.230 --> 2:05:39.863
Everything I tell you to do you do it

2:05:40.297 --> 2:05:42.963
or I will kill you kid, you and Jimmy.

2:05:43.696 --> 2:05:44.729
Do you understand me?

2:05:44.763 --> 2:05:45.396
Yeah, I.

2:05:46.196 --> 2:05:47.196
Yes, sir.

2:05:51.795 --> 2:05:55.594
So, she wants to be dead.

2:05:58.861 --> 2:06:01.327
Aaah. Riff!

2:06:01.327 --> 2:06:04.327
Riff, look at me, we're friends,

2:06:04.360 --> 2:06:05.460
why would you do this?

2:06:06.093 --> 2:06:08.193
Cliff knows Mrs Smart,

2:06:08.193 --> 2:06:09.793
he knows all about your plan.

2:06:10.093 --> 2:06:11.692
How, how does he know?

2:06:12.259 --> 2:06:12.692
I had to tell him

2:06:12.726 --> 2:06:13.625
he was going to kill me.

2:06:14.025 --> 2:06:14.992
Why, oh God.

2:06:14.992 --> 2:06:15.825
What have you done.

2:06:16.925 --> 2:06:18.425
I've got to do this Mrs Smart.

2:06:18.425 --> 2:06:20.591
No, no, Riff, don't you see?

2:06:20.891 --> 2:06:22.624
He's trying to set you up for my murder.

2:06:22.891 --> 2:06:24.357
He is going to kill me.

2:06:24.791 --> 2:06:25.990
Do you hear me, he's

2:06:25.990 --> 2:06:27.424
going to put a bullet in my head

2:06:27.524 --> 2:06:30.323
and not just mine, Jimmys as well.

2:06:30.323 --> 2:06:32.823
This way, this way, he said,

2:06:32.823 --> 2:06:33.856
he is going to leave us alone.

2:06:34.956 --> 2:06:37.756
There's got to be a way out of this Riff.

2:06:37.756 --> 2:06:40.189
I'm so sorry.

2:06:40.189 --> 2:06:42.088
I guess this was my path.

2:06:42.088 --> 2:06:43.421
You could flee.

2:06:43.421 --> 2:06:45.554
You could just pretend

2:06:45.554 --> 2:06:46.388
that you killed me.

2:06:46.721 --> 2:06:47.754
What about Jimmy?

2:06:48.087 --> 2:06:48.987
What about him?

2:06:49.454 --> 2:06:49.854
He loves you.

2:06:49.854 --> 2:06:51.087
You would just leave him?

2:06:53.387 --> 2:06:54.420
He's a sweet kid.

2:06:55.120 --> 2:06:55.753
He's young.

2:06:55.753 --> 2:06:57.586
I don't want him on the run,

2:06:57.586 --> 2:06:58.453
he's got the rest of

2:06:58.453 --> 2:06:59.486
his life ahead of him.

2:07:00.686 --> 2:07:04.785
Oh God, Mr Smart was right.

2:07:04.785 --> 2:07:06.452
He said that you didn't love Jimmy

2:07:06.818 --> 2:07:07.385
because you couldn't

2:07:07.385 --> 2:07:08.551
love anybody but yourself.

2:07:08.885 --> 2:07:09.818
And you needed us to play

2:07:09.818 --> 2:07:11.018
a part in your husband's murder?

2:07:11.251 --> 2:07:12.318
Riff, no!

2:07:13.117 --> 2:07:14.817
I wish he'd never met you.

2:07:15.151 --> 2:07:16.417
I wish none of us had.

2:07:16.884 --> 2:07:18.650
You ruined everything.

2:07:18.950 --> 2:07:19.850
Don't you see that he's

2:07:19.850 --> 2:07:21.550
poisoning your mind against me?

2:07:21.816 --> 2:07:22.183
You know,

2:07:23.516 --> 2:07:25.116
the moment my parents died, I knew,

2:07:26.016 --> 2:07:28.115
I knew that my life would mean nothing,

2:07:28.115 --> 2:07:29.749
that I would mean nothing.

2:07:32.382 --> 2:07:33.448
Something like this was

2:07:33.448 --> 2:07:34.348
inevitable, I guess.

2:07:34.915 --> 2:07:36.548
No Riff, no!

2:07:36.548 --> 2:07:38.447
Goodbye Mrs Smart,

2:07:38.447 --> 2:07:40.614
and may God forgive me.

2:07:41.580 --> 2:07:42.280
Nooooo! Oh,

2:08:07.877 --> 2:08:08.943
(Riff Sobbing)

2:08:18.275 --> 2:08:18.842
It's OK.

2:08:22.308 --> 2:08:23.142
It's OK.

2:08:25.108 --> 2:08:27.508
The hard part's done.

2:08:30.974 --> 2:08:34.607
Cliff, help.

2:08:35.307 --> 2:08:37.806
Help me.

2:08:38.839 --> 2:08:40.872
And why would I do that, sweetheart?

2:08:43.405 --> 2:08:46.205
After you tried to have me killed.

2:08:48.805 --> 2:08:50.471
I'm sorry.

2:08:51.904 --> 2:08:55.071
Oh, I know just how sorry you are.

2:08:56.537 --> 2:09:01.503
My God, all I ever asked from you

2:09:01.670 --> 2:09:03.703
was for you to love me,

2:09:04.469 --> 2:09:05.869
and to give me a child,

2:09:06.036 --> 2:09:08.036
you couldn't even achieve that.

2:09:12.435 --> 2:09:18.867
Have you ever, really loved me Veronica?

2:09:21.767 --> 2:09:24.233
I love you.

2:09:24.467 --> 2:09:27.400
No, no, no, you don't.

2:09:28.766 --> 2:09:30.566
Those are just the desperate words

2:09:30.666 --> 2:09:31.899
of a dying woman.

2:09:36.332 --> 2:09:40.165
I never loved Jimmy.

2:09:41.198 --> 2:09:42.731
I love you.

2:09:44.864 --> 2:09:49.563
No, because you lie as often

2:09:49.563 --> 2:09:51.030
as you breathe baby.

2:10:02.728 --> 2:10:05.061
You get out, you get out of town.

2:10:05.061 --> 2:10:06.428
I don't ever want to see you

2:10:06.428 --> 2:10:07.261
around here again.

2:10:09.894 --> 2:10:12.560
Oh, and Riff.

2:10:12.560 --> 2:10:14.960
Leave the gun here,

2:10:15.960 --> 2:10:18.959
I'll get rid of it,

2:10:20.126 --> 2:10:21.759
I ain't leaving anything to chance.

2:10:25.159 --> 2:10:27.225
Now, get out of here!

2:10:38.857 --> 2:10:39.623
Police.

2:10:44.456 --> 2:10:47.389
Oh God, please.

2:10:48.322 --> 2:10:50.322
There was just some crazy kid here.

2:10:51.688 --> 2:10:53.188
He shot my wife,

2:10:53.188 --> 2:10:55.088
and then he shot me as well.

2:10:55.888 --> 2:10:56.921
Please!

2:11:20.585 --> 2:11:21.184
Oh, God.

2:11:22.684 --> 2:11:24.084
Oh, God, Veronica.

2:11:26.684 --> 2:11:28.384
Who did this to you was it him?

2:11:28.384 --> 2:11:29.417
JImmy?

2:11:29.417 --> 2:11:31.683
Is that you?

2:11:31.683 --> 2:11:32.716
Go....

2:11:32.716 --> 2:11:34.983
I ain't going anywhere.

2:11:34.983 --> 2:11:37.482
I won't let anybody hurt you?

2:11:37.482 --> 2:11:40.349
Take care of you, hold on Veronica.

2:11:40.715 --> 2:11:43.682
No, no, wake up Veronica, wake up?

2:11:45.248 --> 2:11:47.048
You can't.

2:11:47.581 --> 2:11:48.614
You can't die.

2:11:48.614 --> 2:11:50.047
You can't leave me.

2:11:58.413 --> 2:12:00.113
Oh God!

2:12:12.544 --> 2:12:13.378
You see, Jimmy.

2:12:16.177 --> 2:12:17.244
I always win.

2:12:19.710 --> 2:12:23.276
I always have and I always will.

2:12:25.609 --> 2:12:26.209
You killed her.

2:12:27.642 --> 2:12:30.409
You son of a bitch, you killed her!

2:12:30.875 --> 2:12:32.808
No you killed her Jimmy.

2:12:38.474 --> 2:12:40.074
If you want to be a man

2:12:43.040 --> 2:12:43.873
you've got to be able

2:12:43.873 --> 2:12:47.540
to take a shot and not miss,

2:12:50.506 --> 2:12:54.172
and you missed Jimmy,

2:12:55.039 --> 2:12:57.938
it's never wise to miss.

2:12:58.572 --> 2:13:00.371
Give my love to Veronica.

2:13:01.005 --> 2:13:01.738
Wait!

2:13:24.668 --> 2:13:25.635
Oh God!

2:13:32.300 --> 2:13:34.567
Oh my God.

2:13:34.933 --> 2:13:36.833
I thought I told you to go.

2:13:37.500 --> 2:13:39.033
No, no!

2:13:39.266 --> 2:13:40.699
You know what your problem is Riff?

2:13:40.699 --> 2:13:41.832
You care too much.

2:13:42.766 --> 2:13:44.332
Why would you do that?

2:13:44.332 --> 2:13:45.132
You promised.

2:13:46.898 --> 2:13:50.365
Nobody outwits Cliff Smart.

2:13:50.865 --> 2:13:53.764
Now, I um, I tell the police

2:13:53.764 --> 2:13:56.131
that you and Jimmy just just burst in

2:13:56.697 --> 2:13:57.897
and he was screaming

2:13:57.897 --> 2:13:59.930
at her to leave with him, but no,

2:13:59.930 --> 2:14:01.563
she wanted to stay with me

2:14:02.196 --> 2:14:03.696
because she still loves me.

2:14:04.729 --> 2:14:07.829
But he wouldn't have any of that,

2:14:07.829 --> 2:14:08.762
so he shot her,

2:14:09.795 --> 2:14:11.229
but then I shot him,

2:14:11.229 --> 2:14:12.762
in self defence of course.

2:14:13.595 --> 2:14:15.095
Jimmy, Jimmy come on.

2:14:15.695 --> 2:14:19.627
It's too late for him, but you can run.

2:14:20.894 --> 2:14:21.960
I'm letting you run.

2:14:22.260 --> 2:14:23.327
You murdered him.

2:14:23.794 --> 2:14:26.826
He would do anything for her, anything.

2:14:27.793 --> 2:14:28.760
I'm telling the police.

2:14:28.926 --> 2:14:30.059
You're trying to set him up.

2:14:30.926 --> 2:14:32.126
And implicate yourself.

2:14:33.426 --> 2:14:35.192
You ain't stupid enough for that kid.

2:14:35.525 --> 2:14:36.592
I should kill you, right now?

2:14:39.158 --> 2:14:41.158
I don't think your aims that good kid.

2:14:41.591 --> 2:14:43.191
To hell with you Cliff Smart!

2:14:46.457 --> 2:14:47.924
That boy attacked my wife!

2:14:48.724 --> 2:14:50.290
Stop or I'll shoot!

2:15:12.654 --> 2:15:14.154
As I walked around the crime scene,

2:15:14.154 --> 2:15:15.520
I saw Veronica's body

2:15:15.520 --> 2:15:17.586
laid on the floor next to Jimmys.

2:15:17.586 --> 2:15:19.719
A table next to the chair, had an ashtray

2:15:19.719 --> 2:15:21.453
on and a half smoked cigarette.

2:15:22.052 --> 2:15:23.986
Veronica had been caught by surprise,

2:15:24.852 --> 2:15:26.285
Jimmy's body laid next to her

2:15:26.285 --> 2:15:27.918
with his eyes wide open with fear.

2:15:29.418 --> 2:15:31.218
I feel like I died alongside her.

2:15:32.951 --> 2:15:33.951
Does that sound normal?

2:15:34.751 --> 2:15:36.084
I notice that Cliff didn't have

2:15:36.084 --> 2:15:37.384
a single tear in his eye.

2:15:38.350 --> 2:15:39.583
I feel empty.

2:15:40.750 --> 2:15:42.316
I've seen the pain etched in the faces

2:15:42.316 --> 2:15:43.450
of those left behind,

2:15:43.450 --> 2:15:44.649
as reality dawns on them

2:15:44.649 --> 2:15:45.283
that death has changed

2:15:45.283 --> 2:15:45.983
everything for them.

2:15:46.949 --> 2:15:48.516
This should have been

2:15:48.516 --> 2:15:49.715
another routine visit,

2:15:49.715 --> 2:15:51.349
but something about it felt off.

2:15:51.948 --> 2:15:54.515
And it all came down to Cliff Smart.

2:15:54.515 --> 2:15:56.381
Now, Mr. Smart,

2:15:57.514 --> 2:15:59.248
can you tell me if you have any idea

2:15:59.248 --> 2:16:01.247
why these two young men would want

2:16:01.247 --> 2:16:02.880
you and your wife killed?

2:16:05.147 --> 2:16:06.147
Yeah, but

2:16:07.980 --> 2:16:09.213
I don't want to tarnish

2:16:09.213 --> 2:16:10.679
the memory of my wife now.

2:16:10.846 --> 2:16:11.646
She's...

2:16:12.179 --> 2:16:12.712
Dead?

2:16:12.879 --> 2:16:13.446
Yeah.

2:16:16.279 --> 2:16:16.645
I mean,

2:16:18.712 --> 2:16:19.312
well, you see,

2:16:21.145 --> 2:16:23.078
she's been spending a lot of time

2:16:23.078 --> 2:16:25.177
with the kid, Jimmy.

2:16:26.744 --> 2:16:28.277
I think he'd fallen in love with her.

2:16:29.677 --> 2:16:31.943
I'd, um, suspected for a while.

2:16:31.943 --> 2:16:34.442
She used to teach him see,

2:16:34.442 --> 2:16:36.609
she gave him private acting lessons.

2:16:36.609 --> 2:16:38.208
And every time I saw him, like

2:16:39.309 --> 2:16:41.242
I saw the way he looked at her,

2:16:41.242 --> 2:16:42.842
I mean, I hate to say it, but

2:16:44.142 --> 2:16:45.940
at times my um, my wife didn't

2:16:47.141 --> 2:16:49.274
dissuade his flirtations.

2:16:52.007 --> 2:16:54.707
Were the two, intimate?

2:16:56.307 --> 2:16:57.172
Yeah. Yeah,

2:16:59.106 --> 2:16:59.773
I think so.

2:17:01.839 --> 2:17:02.606
I think he thought

2:17:02.606 --> 2:17:03.939
they'd be together in the future.

2:17:04.805 --> 2:17:05.472
You know,

2:17:06.505 --> 2:17:07.738
there was something real strange

2:17:07.738 --> 2:17:09.072
about this kid Detective.

2:17:10.904 --> 2:17:12.838
He had something real dark in his eyes.

2:17:13.738 --> 2:17:16.103
He was clearly, very troubled.

2:17:16.271 --> 2:17:18.136
Did he say anything

2:17:18.136 --> 2:17:19.237
when they turned up tonight?

2:17:19.869 --> 2:17:23.036
He just stormed in in a rage

2:17:23.036 --> 2:17:24.602
and just kept screaming

2:17:24.602 --> 2:17:25.969
that Veronica had to go with him.

2:17:25.969 --> 2:17:28.568
But Veronica just kept saying

2:17:28.568 --> 2:17:30.702
that he was just a little boy and that

2:17:32.101 --> 2:17:33.035
she was married

2:17:34.168 --> 2:17:35.235
and she loved me,

2:17:37.201 --> 2:17:38.268
but he wouldn't accept it.

2:17:39.434 --> 2:17:41.701
He just kept screaming his love for her.

2:17:42.900 --> 2:17:43.867
Eventually he said,

2:17:45.200 --> 2:17:47.332
if I can't have her, then nobody can.

2:17:48.266 --> 2:17:48.900
Oh, God.

2:17:51.766 --> 2:17:52.366
Then he shot her.

2:17:53.966 --> 2:17:55.132
I mean, I tried to shield it,

2:17:55.132 --> 2:17:57.764
but he shot me as well.

2:17:58.932 --> 2:18:03.498
Lucky for me I managed to fall

2:18:03.498 --> 2:18:05.131
near the drawer where I keep my gun.

2:18:05.164 --> 2:18:07.263
So I just about managed

2:18:07.564 --> 2:18:08.897
to let off one shot.

2:18:08.964 --> 2:18:10.230
Straight through the heart.

2:18:10.363 --> 2:18:11.029
I just shot.

2:18:11.029 --> 2:18:11.830
I didn't aim.

2:18:14.929 --> 2:18:16.696
I just wish I could have saved her.

2:18:17.862 --> 2:18:21.462
Still no tears, an actor Cliff was not.

2:18:22.928 --> 2:18:23.962
What about the other boy?

2:18:26.195 --> 2:18:26.695
Oh, yeah.

2:18:28.493 --> 2:18:29.394
He didn't say much.

2:18:31.527 --> 2:18:33.327
I mean, once I'd managed to kill Jimmy,

2:18:33.560 --> 2:18:35.093
in self-defense, um, he, he,

2:18:35.093 --> 2:18:37.526
he ran out of the house,

2:18:39.093 --> 2:18:40.793
and then you fine men turned up.

2:18:41.993 --> 2:18:42.492
I see.

2:18:43.492 --> 2:18:44.026
Well, it all seems

2:18:44.026 --> 2:18:45.325
pretty straightforward to me,

2:18:45.325 --> 2:18:46.659
but you might want to get

2:18:46.659 --> 2:18:47.525
that wound looked at.

2:18:48.558 --> 2:18:51.858
If you ask me, you're very lucky

2:18:51.858 --> 2:18:53.457
it just grazed you.

2:18:53.457 --> 2:18:54.724
God must have intervened.

2:18:57.389 --> 2:18:58.189
Indeed.

2:19:02.256 --> 2:19:04.490
Vivian, please sit down,

2:19:04.490 --> 2:19:05.789
I've got something to tell you.

2:19:05.789 --> 2:19:07.722
Mother, I have to go.

2:19:07.722 --> 2:19:09.022
Veronica never showed last night

2:19:09.022 --> 2:19:09.822
and I can't find Riff.

2:19:09.822 --> 2:19:11.289
I need to make sure that he stops...

2:19:11.455 --> 2:19:12.189
Stops what?

2:19:14.421 --> 2:19:15.088
Teenage drama mother.

2:19:15.555 --> 2:19:16.555
You don't need to know everything.

2:19:17.620 --> 2:19:18.554
Vivian, please.

2:19:18.988 --> 2:19:20.087
It's terribly important.

2:19:20.386 --> 2:19:21.521
I said I have to go.

2:19:22.154 --> 2:19:23.520
Mrs Smart.

2:19:25.587 --> 2:19:27.020
She's dead.

2:19:31.053 --> 2:19:34.419
Vivian, oh Vivian.

2:19:38.185 --> 2:19:42.084
Jimmy's also dead, and Riff, well,

2:19:43.618 --> 2:19:44.418
it's not looking good

2:19:44.418 --> 2:19:45.451
for him, he's in a coma.

2:19:46.617 --> 2:19:47.350
What?

2:19:48.750 --> 2:19:49.384
They were murdered

2:19:49.384 --> 2:19:50.550
last night at her home.

2:19:50.550 --> 2:19:51.450
They say... What?

2:19:51.650 --> 2:19:53.815
What do they say?

2:19:56.483 --> 2:19:58.582
They say that Jimmy was in love with her.

2:20:00.015 --> 2:20:01.449
She turned him down

2:20:01.449 --> 2:20:03.215
and Jimmy shot Veronica.

2:20:03.215 --> 2:20:04.348
Cliff got off one shot

2:20:04.348 --> 2:20:05.814
and then shot Jimmy dead?

2:20:06.181 --> 2:20:07.914
No, you're lying,

2:20:08.481 --> 2:20:11.014
Cliff is dead, Cliff Smart is dead.

2:20:11.714 --> 2:20:13.080
Cliff's fine. No, you're lying.

2:20:13.114 --> 2:20:14.614
I don't lie Vivian.

2:20:15.113 --> 2:20:17.446
How could she be dead,

2:20:18.246 --> 2:20:20.512
and how could Jimmy kill her,

2:20:20.512 --> 2:20:23.112
he couldn't, he wouldn't kill her.

2:20:23.712 --> 2:20:25.445
Sometimes you don't see what's going on

2:20:25.445 --> 2:20:26.112
even with the people

2:20:26.145 --> 2:20:27.244
that you're closest to.

2:20:27.712 --> 2:20:29.712
Riff, oh, God.

2:20:30.111 --> 2:20:31.911
Riff why didn't you stop it,

2:20:31.911 --> 2:20:32.844
why did you join in?

2:20:34.011 --> 2:20:35.277
Oh Vivian, what can I do?

2:20:36.277 --> 2:20:37.344
He took her from me.

2:20:38.077 --> 2:20:38.844
From us.

2:20:40.010 --> 2:20:42.343
Jimmy was obviously very confused.

2:20:43.276 --> 2:20:44.643
She was my only friend.

2:20:46.343 --> 2:20:47.576
She was the only person

2:20:47.576 --> 2:20:48.742
who ever believed in me.

2:20:48.909 --> 2:20:49.842
That's not true.

2:20:49.842 --> 2:20:51.275
I've always believed in you.

2:20:51.275 --> 2:20:54.175
How can she not be here anymore.

2:20:54.608 --> 2:20:56.575
Oh God mother, it hurts.

2:20:59.974 --> 2:21:01.007
it's OK.

2:21:01.374 --> 2:21:02.074
It's OK.

2:21:02.141 --> 2:21:06.607
It's OK to be sad.

2:21:06.939 --> 2:21:07.740
Sad?

2:21:08.606 --> 2:21:10.839
Sad, he took her from me.

2:21:11.839 --> 2:21:14.606
Oh, no, my head is spinning.

2:21:14.905 --> 2:21:16.005
God, mother

2:21:16.005 --> 2:21:17.738
she was my ticket out of here,

2:21:17.738 --> 2:21:19.538
she was going to make me a star.

2:21:22.005 --> 2:21:23.871
Let me get you some hot tea.

2:21:23.871 --> 2:21:25.604
I don't need hot tea.

2:21:25.604 --> 2:21:27.404
I need to make him pay.

2:21:28.437 --> 2:21:30.037
Jimmy paid with his life, Vivian.

2:21:30.737 --> 2:21:31.303
Jimmy?

2:21:31.303 --> 2:21:34.203
Oh mother, you have no idea

2:21:34.270 --> 2:21:35.569
what you're talking about.

2:21:35.569 --> 2:21:37.003
Then talk to me, please.

2:21:37.003 --> 2:21:38.702
Mother, I need to be alone.

2:21:40.135 --> 2:21:40.669
Vivian, please.

2:21:40.669 --> 2:21:42.902
I said, get out, mother,

2:21:43.101 --> 2:21:44.768
get out, get out, get out.

2:21:45.368 --> 2:21:47.401
I never want to see you again.

2:21:47.401 --> 2:21:49.668
Get out, I never want to see you anymore.

2:21:53.167 --> 2:21:53.967
No.

2:22:00.332 --> 2:22:01.799
Oh God. No. No.

2:22:04.866 --> 2:22:06.465
How can he do this.

2:22:38.028 --> 2:22:39.828
The innocence of youth was lost.

2:22:40.394 --> 2:22:41.094
The paths they took

2:22:41.094 --> 2:22:42.661
led to their own downfall.

2:22:43.493 --> 2:22:44.660
Veronica had destroyed

2:22:44.694 --> 2:22:46.260
everybody to get what she wanted

2:22:46.860 --> 2:22:48.626
and if she went to hell, I'm

2:22:48.626 --> 2:22:49.725
sure even the devil

2:22:49.725 --> 2:22:50.725
wouldn't recognize her.

2:22:51.593 --> 2:22:52.593
It's two days later

2:22:53.026 --> 2:22:54.026
and Cliff was finished

2:22:54.026 --> 2:22:55.225
playing the grieving husband.

2:22:55.659 --> 2:22:57.492
In fact, Cliff had a secret of his own.

2:23:01.690 --> 2:23:02.658
Get over here, baby.

2:23:03.824 --> 2:23:05.557
I got you a brandy darling

2:23:05.557 --> 2:23:06.491
just how you like it.

2:23:06.991 --> 2:23:08.757
God, I'm so grateful

2:23:08.757 --> 2:23:09.957
to have you at my side.

2:23:11.257 --> 2:23:13.655
So, Cliff, Veronica never knew.

2:23:13.990 --> 2:23:15.422
She never knew that we didn't break up?

2:23:15.889 --> 2:23:16.756
Never had a clue.

2:23:17.356 --> 2:23:18.889
Went to her grave, none the wiser.

2:23:19.822 --> 2:23:20.755
I still can't believe

2:23:20.755 --> 2:23:22.322
she was murdered in this house.

2:23:22.522 --> 2:23:24.421
Yeah, tough break.

2:23:25.455 --> 2:23:27.755
I mean, we had our disagreements, but

2:23:28.788 --> 2:23:29.721
I never wanted her dead,

2:23:30.421 --> 2:23:31.386
even after all she did.

2:23:31.921 --> 2:23:34.087
You are handling it so well.

2:23:34.554 --> 2:23:35.886
It can't be easy for you.

2:23:36.853 --> 2:23:38.619
The pain will always be there.

2:23:38.619 --> 2:23:39.886
And that's because you're such

2:23:39.886 --> 2:23:41.019
a good man, Cliff Smart.

2:23:41.353 --> 2:23:42.553
And you're going to make

2:23:42.553 --> 2:23:44.252
a wonderful father to our baby.

2:23:45.019 --> 2:23:46.919
A little Cliff running around.

2:23:46.919 --> 2:23:48.085
Or Lana.

2:23:48.818 --> 2:23:49.718
I'm so grateful

2:23:49.718 --> 2:23:51.151
you decided against doing your show.

2:23:51.151 --> 2:23:53.918
Now you're with child.

2:23:53.918 --> 2:23:55.451
No wife of mine will be

2:23:55.451 --> 2:23:56.317
burdened with work.

2:23:57.517 --> 2:23:58.884
You're a housewife and a mother.

2:23:59.984 --> 2:24:01.117
The greatest job there is.

2:24:03.016 --> 2:24:04.315
Are you expecting anybody?

2:24:05.183 --> 2:24:05.483
No.

2:24:05.815 --> 2:24:07.216
Don't you move, I'll get it.

2:24:07.216 --> 2:24:09.116
You'll do nothing of the sort.

2:24:09.116 --> 2:24:10.182
Let me get it.

2:24:10.182 --> 2:24:11.582
I'll be waiting in the bedroom for you

2:24:11.582 --> 2:24:12.182
Cliffy.

2:24:12.615 --> 2:24:13.282
Lana.

2:24:14.482 --> 2:24:15.415
I ain't going to waste

2:24:15.415 --> 2:24:16.448
my second chance at love, baby.

2:24:23.514 --> 2:24:24.614
Cliff reached out for

2:24:24.614 --> 2:24:26.347
the door and opened it,

2:24:26.947 --> 2:24:29.279
and so his surprise, he sees Veronica

2:24:29.279 --> 2:24:30.746
stood there with her back to him.

2:24:31.646 --> 2:24:32.546
He's taken aback,

2:24:33.179 --> 2:24:34.312
but a moment later,

2:24:34.312 --> 2:24:35.612
the woman turns around

2:24:35.612 --> 2:24:36.645
and it's not Veronica.

2:24:37.011 --> 2:24:38.845
It's Vivian, dressed

2:24:38.845 --> 2:24:40.212
in a killer red dress,

2:24:40.212 --> 2:24:42.145
she looks just like Veronica.

2:24:44.044 --> 2:24:45.278
What the hell do you want?

2:24:46.711 --> 2:24:47.844
Why are you dressed like that?

2:24:48.177 --> 2:24:50.444
Well, Cliffy, I have a message for you.

2:24:51.310 --> 2:24:52.410
Who is it, sweetheart?

2:24:53.510 --> 2:24:54.576
Well what the hell kind of message

2:24:54.576 --> 2:24:55.410
would you have for me?

2:24:56.009 --> 2:24:57.176
It's simple, Cliffy.

2:24:57.609 --> 2:24:58.342
It's from Veronica.

2:24:59.475 --> 2:25:00.742
Veronica's dead.

2:25:00.742 --> 2:25:04.475
Yes Cliffy, and she's real mad about it.

2:25:23.306 --> 2:25:24.339
LANA!!

2:25:25.405 --> 2:25:26.572
Aaaahhhhh!!!

2:25:49.402 --> 2:25:50.101
Vivian would be arrested

2:25:50.601 --> 2:25:52.235
and sent to a mental institution

2:25:52.469 --> 2:25:54.235
where she would remain for years.

2:25:56.768 --> 2:25:58.901
Vivian Pierce, this sweet girl

2:25:58.901 --> 2:26:00.668
with a bright future ahead of her

2:26:00.668 --> 2:26:01.867
had now vanished.

2:26:02.434 --> 2:26:03.567
All that was left,

2:26:03.567 --> 2:26:05.333
a broken shell of a girl

2:26:05.634 --> 2:26:07.067
who soul seems to have been

2:26:07.067 --> 2:26:08.933
completely removed from her body.

2:26:09.500 --> 2:26:10.832
Her mother and loyal friend

2:26:10.832 --> 2:26:12.133
will be her only visitors.

2:26:12.499 --> 2:26:15.099
And even then, Jean never gets to truly

2:26:15.466 --> 2:26:16.132
see her daughter.

2:26:17.564 --> 2:26:18.232
It would be a week later,

2:26:18.598 --> 2:26:21.331
when Riff opened his eyes, and his mouth.

2:26:22.365 --> 2:26:24.530
Yeah, he told us the whole sordid story.

2:26:25.030 --> 2:26:26.231
It was only at that moment

2:26:26.431 --> 2:26:27.731
that everything fell into place.

2:26:28.231 --> 2:26:29.630
The affair, the murder

2:26:29.630 --> 2:26:31.097
plot, thedouble cross.

2:26:31.097 --> 2:26:32.330
It was something that

2:26:32.330 --> 2:26:33.696
even the best Hollywood writers

2:26:33.696 --> 2:26:34.363
ccoudn't have dreamed up.

2:26:36.229 --> 2:26:37.896
Riff would be sent to jail for 10 years

2:26:37.896 --> 2:26:39.396
for the murder of Veronica Smart.

2:26:39.962 --> 2:26:40.994
But he's using the time

2:26:40.994 --> 2:26:42.462
to better himself,

2:26:42.462 --> 2:26:44.162
to learn himself a trade.

2:26:44.162 --> 2:26:45.994
God, please let one positive come

2:26:45.994 --> 2:26:46.728
from this tragedy.

2:26:47.728 --> 2:26:48.928
In all my years,

2:26:48.928 --> 2:26:49.828
I had never seen a more

2:26:49.828 --> 2:26:51.327
twisted or tragic story

2:26:51.827 --> 2:26:53.527
from one teenage boys fantasy

2:26:53.794 --> 2:26:55.794
and one manipulative woman's motives came

2:26:55.794 --> 2:26:57.027
the murders of Jimmy Flynn,

2:26:57.327 --> 2:26:59.126
Cliff Smart and Veronica Smart.

2:26:59.793 --> 2:27:01.458
The tragedy wouldn't end there, however,

2:27:01.458 --> 2:27:03.859
the implications were far and wide.

2:27:04.192 --> 2:27:05.392
It would be too much for Harvey.

2:27:05.892 --> 2:27:08.359
He will blame himself for how hard

2:27:08.359 --> 2:27:09.725
he had been towards his son, a charge

2:27:09.725 --> 2:27:10.858
he was sadly guilty of.

2:27:11.358 --> 2:27:13.291
So on a cold winter night,

2:27:13.690 --> 2:27:15.291
Harvey Flynn took a large drink

2:27:15.291 --> 2:27:16.324
from his bottle of whiskey,

2:27:16.891 --> 2:27:17.891
picks up his pistol,

2:27:18.291 --> 2:27:19.724
aimed it at his head and.

2:27:21.257 --> 2:27:23.323
Well, he didn't pull the trigger,

2:27:24.123 --> 2:27:24.890
stopping himself

2:27:24.890 --> 2:27:26.155
becoming the latest victim

2:27:26.155 --> 2:27:26.922
of this tragedy.

2:27:28.522 --> 2:27:30.789
As for me, well, I left the force.

2:27:31.689 --> 2:27:33.522
The case lingered over every move I made.

2:27:34.322 --> 2:27:35.488
This ain't like the movies,

2:27:35.822 --> 2:27:37.521
the detective doesn't always get his man.

2:27:38.421 --> 2:27:40.288
So now I write pulp detective novels

2:27:40.654 --> 2:27:42.787
like this one you witnessed, it's

2:27:42.787 --> 2:27:44.720
cathartic in a way, it helps me release

2:27:44.820 --> 2:27:45.820
the nightmares I see

2:27:45.820 --> 2:27:47.053
in my sleep to the page.

2:27:47.053 --> 2:27:49.186
It helps me to put them to bed for good.

2:27:50.186 --> 2:27:51.153
Now it's your nightmare.

2:27:52.553 --> 2:27:54.618
You see, the city is a scary place.

2:27:54.618 --> 2:27:56.152
nobody is what they seem.

2:27:56.851 --> 2:27:58.419
Evil doesn't always hide around

2:27:58.419 --> 2:28:00.185
dark corners, and innocence

2:28:01.018 --> 2:28:03.218
doesn't automatically mean innocent.

2:28:03.218 --> 2:28:05.684
People are far more complex than that.

2:28:06.583 --> 2:28:07.284
In this case,

2:28:08.550 --> 2:28:09.850
they showed me the horrific acts

2:28:09.850 --> 2:28:11.283
that people can do to one another

2:28:12.017 --> 2:28:13.050
over a beautiful

2:28:13.383 --> 2:28:14.483
but unworthy woman.

2:28:15.850 --> 2:28:17.916
See, nobody is truly bad

2:28:17.916 --> 2:28:19.682
or good, right or wrong.

2:28:20.382 --> 2:28:21.482
Human existence is far

2:28:21.482 --> 2:28:22.715
more complicated than that.

2:28:23.748 --> 2:28:25.314
And that's the scariest thing of all,

2:28:26.314 --> 2:28:27.748
because you can never see it coming.

2:28:29.414 --> 2:28:30.280
This is my city,

2:28:31.247 --> 2:28:32.447
and I prided myself on

2:28:32.447 --> 2:28:33.614
solving every case

2:28:33.614 --> 2:28:34.779
that came across my desk.

2:28:35.779 --> 2:28:36.813
Well, apart from one,

2:28:37.613 --> 2:28:39.180
the case of Veronica Smart,

2:28:40.546 --> 2:28:41.546
a woman who destroyed

2:28:41.546 --> 2:28:42.813
everything that got in her way.
